75/// This takes an arbitrary SelectionDAG as input and
76/// hacks on it until the target machine can handle it. This involves
77/// eliminating value sizes the machine cannot handle (promoting small sizes to
78/// large sizes or splitting up large values into small values) as well as
79/// eliminating operations the machine cannot handle.
80///
81/// This code also does a small amount of optimization and recognition of idioms
82/// as part of its processing. For example, if a target does not support a
83/// 'setcc' instruction efficiently, but does support 'brcc' instruction, this
84/// will attempt merge setcc and brc instructions into brcc's.
85class SelectionDAGLegalize {
86 const TargetMachine &TM;
87 const TargetLowering &TLI;
88 SelectionDAG &DAG;
89
90 /// The set of nodes which have already been legalized. We hold a
91 /// reference to it in order to update as necessary on node deletion.
92 SmallPtrSetImpl<SDNode *> &LegalizedNodes;
93
94 /// A set of all the nodes updated during legalization.
95 SmallSetVector<SDNode *, 16> *UpdatedNodes;
96
97 EVT getSetCCResultType(EVT VT) const {
98 return TLI.getSetCCResultType(DAG.getDataLayout(), *DAG.getContext(), VT);
99 }
100
101 // Libcall insertion helpers.
102
103public:
104 SelectionDAGLegalize(SelectionDAG &DAG,
105 SmallPtrSetImpl<SDNode *> &LegalizedNodes,
106 SmallSetVector<SDNode *, 16> *UpdatedNodes = nullptr)
107 : TM(DAG.getTarget()), TLI(DAG.getTargetLoweringInfo()), DAG(DAG),
108 LegalizedNodes(LegalizedNodes), UpdatedNodes(UpdatedNodes) {}
109
110 /// Legalizes the given operation.
111 void LegalizeOp(SDNode *Node);
112
113private:
114 SDValue OptimizeFloatStore(StoreSDNode *ST);
115
116 void LegalizeLoadOps(SDNode *Node);
117 void LegalizeStoreOps(SDNode *Node);
118
119 /// Some targets cannot handle a variable
120 /// insertion index for the INSERT_VECTOR_ELT instruction. In this case, it
121 /// is necessary to spill the vector being inserted into to memory, perform
122 /// the insert there, and then read the result back.
123 SDValue PerformInsertVectorEltInMemory(SDValue Vec, SDValue Val, SDValue Idx,
124 const SDLoc &dl);
125 SDValue ExpandINSERT_VECTOR_ELT(SDValue Vec, SDValue Val, SDValue Idx,
126 const SDLoc &dl);
127
128 /// Return a vector shuffle operation which
129 /// performs the same shuffe in terms of order or result bytes, but on a type
130 /// whose vector element type is narrower than the original shuffle type.
131 /// e.g. <v4i32> <0, 1, 0, 1> -> v8i16 <0, 1, 2, 3, 0, 1, 2, 3>
132 SDValue ShuffleWithNarrowerEltType(EVT NVT, EVT VT, const SDLoc &dl,
133 SDValue N1, SDValue N2,
134 ArrayRef<int> Mask) const;
135
136 bool LegalizeSetCCCondCode(EVT VT, SDValue &LHS, SDValue &RHS, SDValue &CC,
137 bool &NeedInvert, const SDLoc &dl);
138
139 SDValue ExpandLibCall(RTLIB::Libcall LC, SDNode *Node, bool isSigned);
140
141 std::pair<SDValue, SDValue> ExpandChainLibCall(RTLIB::Libcall LC,
142 SDNode *Node, bool isSigned);
143 SDValue ExpandFPLibCall(SDNode *Node, RTLIB::Libcall Call_F32,
144 RTLIB::Libcall Call_F64, RTLIB::Libcall Call_F80,
145 RTLIB::Libcall Call_F128,
146 RTLIB::Libcall Call_PPCF128);
147 SDValue ExpandIntLibCall(SDNode *Node, bool isSigned,
148 RTLIB::Libcall Call_I8,
149 RTLIB::Libcall Call_I16,
150 RTLIB::Libcall Call_I32,
151 RTLIB::Libcall Call_I64,
152 RTLIB::Libcall Call_I128);
153 SDValue ExpandArgFPLibCall(SDNode *Node,
154 RTLIB::Libcall Call_F32, RTLIB::Libcall Call_F64,
155 RTLIB::Libcall Call_F80, RTLIB::Libcall Call_F128,
156 RTLIB::Libcall Call_PPCF128);
157 void ExpandDivRemLibCall(SDNode *Node, SmallVectorImpl<SDValue> &Results);
158 void ExpandSinCosLibCall(SDNode *Node, SmallVectorImpl<SDValue> &Results);
159
160 SDValue EmitStackConvert(SDValue SrcOp, EVT SlotVT, EVT DestVT,
161 const SDLoc &dl);
162 SDValue EmitStackConvert(SDValue SrcOp, EVT SlotVT, EVT DestVT,
163 const SDLoc &dl, SDValue ChainIn);
164 SDValue ExpandBUILD_VECTOR(SDNode *Node);
165 SDValue ExpandSCALAR_TO_VECTOR(SDNode *Node);
166 void ExpandDYNAMIC_STACKALLOC(SDNode *Node,
167 SmallVectorImpl<SDValue> &Results);
168 void getSignAsIntValue(FloatSignAsInt &State, const SDLoc &DL,
169 SDValue Value) const;
170 SDValue modifySignAsInt(const FloatSignAsInt &State, const SDLoc &DL,
171 SDValue NewIntValue) const;
172 SDValue ExpandFCOPYSIGN(SDNode *Node) const;
173 SDValue ExpandFABS(SDNode *Node) const;
174 SDValue ExpandLegalINT_TO_FP(bool isSigned, SDValue Op0, EVT DestVT,
175 const SDLoc &dl);
176 SDValue PromoteLegalINT_TO_FP(SDValue LegalOp, EVT DestVT, bool isSigned,
177 const SDLoc &dl);
178 SDValue PromoteLegalFP_TO_INT(SDValue LegalOp, EVT DestVT, bool isSigned,
179 const SDLoc &dl);
180
181 SDValue ExpandBITREVERSE(SDValue Op, const SDLoc &dl);
182 SDValue ExpandBSWAP(SDValue Op, const SDLoc &dl);
183
184 SDValue ExpandExtractFromVectorThroughStack(SDValue Op);
185 SDValue ExpandInsertToVectorThroughStack(SDValue Op);
186 SDValue ExpandVectorBuildThroughStack(SDNode* Node);
187
188 SDValue ExpandConstantFP(ConstantFPSDNode *CFP, bool UseCP);
189 SDValue ExpandConstant(ConstantSDNode *CP);
190
191 // if ExpandNode returns false, LegalizeOp falls back to ConvertNodeToLibcall
192 bool ExpandNode(SDNode *Node);
193 void ConvertNodeToLibcall(SDNode *Node);
194 void PromoteNode(SDNode *Node);
195
196public:
197 // Node replacement helpers
198
199 void ReplacedNode(SDNode *N) {
200 LegalizedNodes.erase(N);
201 if (UpdatedNodes)
202 UpdatedNodes->insert(N);
203 }
204
205 void ReplaceNode(SDNode *Old, SDNode *New) {
206 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " ... replacing: "; Old->dump(&DAG);
207 dbgs() << " with: "; New->dump(&DAG));
208
209 assert(Old->getNumValues() == New->getNumValues() &&
210 "Replacing one node with another that produces a different number "
211 "of values!");
212 DAG.ReplaceAllUsesWith(Old, New);
213 if (UpdatedNodes)
214 UpdatedNodes->insert(New);
215 ReplacedNode(Old);
216 }
217
218 void ReplaceNode(SDValue Old, SDValue New) {
219 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " ... replacing: "; Old->dump(&DAG);
220 dbgs() << " with: "; New->dump(&DAG));
221
222 DAG.ReplaceAllUsesWith(Old, New);
223 if (UpdatedNodes)
224 UpdatedNodes->insert(New.getNode());
225 ReplacedNode(Old.getNode());
226 }
227
228 void ReplaceNode(SDNode *Old, const SDValue *New) {
229 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " ... replacing: "; Old->dump(&DAG));
230
231 DAG.ReplaceAllUsesWith(Old, New);
232 for (unsigned i = 0, e = Old->getNumValues(); i != e; ++i) {
233 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << (i == 0 ? " with: " : " and: ");
234 New[i]->dump(&DAG));
235 if (UpdatedNodes)
236 UpdatedNodes->insert(New[i].getNode());
237 }
238 ReplacedNode(Old);
239 }
240};
241
242} // end anonymous namespace

244/// Return a vector shuffle operation which
245/// performs the same shuffle in terms of order or result bytes, but on a type
246/// whose vector element type is narrower than the original shuffle type.
247/// e.g. <v4i32> <0, 1, 0, 1> -> v8i16 <0, 1, 2, 3, 0, 1, 2, 3>
248SDValue SelectionDAGLegalize::ShuffleWithNarrowerEltType(
249 EVT NVT, EVT VT, const SDLoc &dl, SDValue N1, SDValue N2,
250 ArrayRef<int> Mask) const {
251 unsigned NumMaskElts = VT.getVectorNumElements();
252 unsigned NumDestElts = NVT.getVectorNumElements();
253 unsigned NumEltsGrowth = NumDestElts / NumMaskElts;
254
255 assert(NumEltsGrowth && "Cannot promote to vector type with fewer elts!");
256
257 if (NumEltsGrowth == 1)
258 return DAG.getVectorShuffle(NVT, dl, N1, N2, Mask);
259
260 SmallVector<int, 8> NewMask;
261 for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumMaskElts; ++i) {
262 int Idx = Mask[i];
263 for (unsigned j = 0; j != NumEltsGrowth; ++j) {
264 if (Idx < 0)
265 NewMask.push_back(-1);
266 else
267 NewMask.push_back(Idx * NumEltsGrowth + j);
268 }
269 }
270 assert(NewMask.size() == NumDestElts && "Non-integer NumEltsGrowth?");
271 assert(TLI.isShuffleMaskLegal(NewMask, NVT) && "Shuffle not legal?");
272 return DAG.getVectorShuffle(NVT, dl, N1, N2, NewMask);
273}

275/// Expands the ConstantFP node to an integer constant or
276/// a load from the constant pool.
277SDValue
278SelectionDAGLegalize::ExpandConstantFP(ConstantFPSDNode *CFP, bool UseCP) {
279 bool Extend = false;
280 SDLoc dl(CFP);
281
282 // If a FP immediate is precise when represented as a float and if the
283 // target can do an extending load from float to double, we put it into
284 // the constant pool as a float, even if it's is statically typed as a
285 // double. This shrinks FP constants and canonicalizes them for targets where
286 // an FP extending load is the same cost as a normal load (such as on the x87
287 // fp stack or PPC FP unit).
288 EVT VT = CFP->getValueType(0);
289 ConstantFP *LLVMC = const_cast<ConstantFP*>(CFP->getConstantFPValue());
290 if (!UseCP) {
291 assert((VT == MVT::f64 || VT == MVT::f32) && "Invalid type expansion");
292 return DAG.getConstant(LLVMC->getValueAPF().bitcastToAPInt(), dl,
293 (VT == MVT::f64) ? MVT::i64 : MVT::i32);
294 }
295
296 APFloat APF = CFP->getValueAPF();
297 EVT OrigVT = VT;
298 EVT SVT = VT;
299
300 // We don't want to shrink SNaNs. Converting the SNaN back to its real type
301 // can cause it to be changed into a QNaN on some platforms (e.g. on SystemZ).
302 if (!APF.isSignaling()) {
303 while (SVT != MVT::f32 && SVT != MVT::f16) {
304 SVT = (MVT::SimpleValueType)(SVT.getSimpleVT().SimpleTy - 1);
305 if (ConstantFPSDNode::isValueValidForType(SVT, APF) &&
306 // Only do this if the target has a native EXTLOAD instruction from
307 // smaller type.
308 TLI.isLoadExtLegal(ISD::EXTLOAD, OrigVT, SVT) &&
309 TLI.ShouldShrinkFPConstant(OrigVT)) {
310 Type *SType = SVT.getTypeForEVT(*DAG.getContext());
311 LLVMC = cast<ConstantFP>(ConstantExpr::getFPTrunc(LLVMC, SType));
312 VT = SVT;
313 Extend = true;
314 }
315 }
316 }
317
318 SDValue CPIdx = DAG.getConstantPool(
319 LLVMC, TLI.getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout(),
320 DAG.getDataLayout().getGlobalsAddressSpace()));
321 unsigned Alignment = cast<ConstantPoolSDNode>(CPIdx)->getAlignment();
322 if (Extend) {
323 SDValue Result = DAG.getExtLoad(
324 ISD::EXTLOAD, dl, OrigVT, DAG.getEntryNode(), CPIdx,
325 MachinePointerInfo::getConstantPool(DAG.getMachineFunction()), VT,
326 Alignment);
327 return Result;
328 }
329 SDValue Result = DAG.getLoad(
330 OrigVT, dl, DAG.getEntryNode(), CPIdx,
331 MachinePointerInfo::getConstantPool(DAG.getMachineFunction()), Alignment);
332 return Result;
333}
334
335/// Expands the Constant node to a load from the constant pool.
336SDValue SelectionDAGLegalize::ExpandConstant(ConstantSDNode *CP) {
337 SDLoc dl(CP);
338 EVT VT = CP->getValueType(0);
339 SDValue CPIdx = DAG.getConstantPool(
340 CP->getConstantIntValue(),
341 TLI.getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout(),
342 DAG.getDataLayout().getGlobalsAddressSpace()));
343 unsigned Alignment = cast<ConstantPoolSDNode>(CPIdx)->getAlignment();
344 SDValue Result = DAG.getLoad(
345 VT, dl, DAG.getEntryNode(), CPIdx,
346 MachinePointerInfo::getConstantPool(DAG.getMachineFunction()), Alignment);
347 return Result;
348}

350/// Some target cannot handle a variable insertion index for the
351/// INSERT_VECTOR_ELT instruction. In this case, it
352/// is necessary to spill the vector being inserted into to memory, perform
353/// the insert there, and then read the result back.
354SDValue SelectionDAGLegalize::PerformInsertVectorEltInMemory(SDValue Vec,
355 SDValue Val,
356 SDValue Idx,
357 const SDLoc &dl) {
358 SDValue Tmp1 = Vec;
359 SDValue Tmp2 = Val;
360 SDValue Tmp3 = Idx;
361
362 // If the target doesn't support this, we have to spill the input vector
363 // to a temporary stack slot, update the element, then reload it. This is
364 // badness. We could also load the value into a vector register (either
365 // with a "move to register" or "extload into register" instruction, then
366 // permute it into place, if the idx is a constant and if the idx is
367 // supported by the target.
368 EVT VT = Tmp1.getValueType();
369 EVT EltVT = VT.getVectorElementType();
370 SDValue StackPtr = DAG.CreateStackTemporary(VT);
371
372 int SPFI = cast<FrameIndexSDNode>(StackPtr.getNode())->getIndex();
373
374 // Store the vector.
375 SDValue Ch = DAG.getStore(
376 DAG.getEntryNode(), dl, Tmp1, StackPtr,
377 MachinePointerInfo::getFixedStack(DAG.getMachineFunction(), SPFI));
378
379 SDValue StackPtr2 = TLI.getVectorElementPointer(DAG, StackPtr, VT, Tmp3);
380
381 // Store the scalar value.
382 Ch = DAG.getTruncStore(Ch, dl, Tmp2, StackPtr2, MachinePointerInfo(), EltVT);
383 // Load the updated vector.
384 return DAG.getLoad(VT, dl, Ch, StackPtr, MachinePointerInfo::getFixedStack(
385 DAG.getMachineFunction(), SPFI));
386}
387
388SDValue SelectionDAGLegalize::ExpandINSERT_VECTOR_ELT(SDValue Vec, SDValue Val,
389 SDValue Idx,
390 const SDLoc &dl) {
391 if (ConstantSDNode *InsertPos = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(Idx)) {
392 // SCALAR_TO_VECTOR requires that the type of the value being inserted
393 // match the element type of the vector being created, except for
394 // integers in which case the inserted value can be over width.
395 EVT EltVT = Vec.getValueType().getVectorElementType();
396 if (Val.getValueType() == EltVT ||
397 (EltVT.isInteger() && Val.getValueType().bitsGE(EltVT))) {
398 SDValue ScVec = DAG.getNode(ISD::SCALAR_TO_VECTOR, dl,
399 Vec.getValueType(), Val);
400
401 unsigned NumElts = Vec.getValueType().getVectorNumElements();
402 // We generate a shuffle of InVec and ScVec, so the shuffle mask
403 // should be 0,1,2,3,4,5... with the appropriate element replaced with
404 // elt 0 of the RHS.
405 SmallVector<int, 8> ShufOps;
406 for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumElts; ++i)
407 ShufOps.push_back(i != InsertPos->getZExtValue() ? i : NumElts);
408
409 return DAG.getVectorShuffle(Vec.getValueType(), dl, Vec, ScVec, ShufOps);
410 }
411 }
412 return PerformInsertVectorEltInMemory(Vec, Val, Idx, dl);
413}

415SDValue SelectionDAGLegalize::OptimizeFloatStore(StoreSDNode* ST) {
416 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Optimizing float store operations\n");
417 // Turn 'store float 1.0, Ptr' -> 'store int 0x12345678, Ptr'
418 // FIXME: We shouldn't do this for TargetConstantFP's.
419 // FIXME: move this to the DAG Combiner! Note that we can't regress due
420 // to phase ordering between legalized code and the dag combiner. This
421 // probably means that we need to integrate dag combiner and legalizer
422 // together.
423 // We generally can't do this one for long doubles.
424 SDValue Chain = ST->getChain();
425 SDValue Ptr = ST->getBasePtr();
426 unsigned Alignment = ST->getAlignment();
427 MachineMemOperand::Flags MMOFlags = ST->getMemOperand()->getFlags();
428 AAMDNodes AAInfo = ST->getAAInfo();
429 SDLoc dl(ST);
430 if (ConstantFPSDNode *CFP = dyn_cast<ConstantFPSDNode>(ST->getValue())) {
431 if (CFP->getValueType(0) == MVT::f32 &&
432 TLI.isTypeLegal(MVT::i32)) {
433 SDValue Con = DAG.getConstant(CFP->getValueAPF().
434 bitcastToAPInt().zextOrTrunc(32),
435 SDLoc(CFP), MVT::i32);
436 return DAG.getStore(Chain, dl, Con, Ptr, ST->getPointerInfo(), Alignment,
437 MMOFlags, AAInfo);
438 }
439
440 if (CFP->getValueType(0) == MVT::f64) {
441 // If this target supports 64-bit registers, do a single 64-bit store.
442 if (TLI.isTypeLegal(MVT::i64)) {
443 SDValue Con = DAG.getConstant(CFP->getValueAPF().bitcastToAPInt().
444 zextOrTrunc(64), SDLoc(CFP), MVT::i64);
445 return DAG.getStore(Chain, dl, Con, Ptr, ST->getPointerInfo(),
446 Alignment, MMOFlags, AAInfo);
447 }
448
449 if (TLI.isTypeLegal(MVT::i32) && !ST->isVolatile()) {
450 // Otherwise, if the target supports 32-bit registers, use 2 32-bit
451 // stores. If the target supports neither 32- nor 64-bits, this
452 // xform is certainly not worth it.
453 const APInt &IntVal = CFP->getValueAPF().bitcastToAPInt();
454 SDValue Lo = DAG.getConstant(IntVal.trunc(32), dl, MVT::i32);
455 SDValue Hi = DAG.getConstant(IntVal.lshr(32).trunc(32), dl, MVT::i32);
456 if (DAG.getDataLayout().isBigEndian())
457 std::swap(Lo, Hi);
458
459 Lo = DAG.getStore(Chain, dl, Lo, Ptr, ST->getPointerInfo(), Alignment,
460 MMOFlags, AAInfo);
461 Ptr = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, dl, Ptr.getValueType(), Ptr,
462 DAG.getConstant(4, dl, Ptr.getValueType()));
463 Hi = DAG.getStore(Chain, dl, Hi, Ptr,
464 ST->getPointerInfo().getWithOffset(4),
465 MinAlign(Alignment, 4U), MMOFlags, AAInfo);
466
467 return DAG.getNode(ISD::TokenFactor, dl, MVT::Other, Lo, Hi);
468 }
469 }
470 }
471 return SDValue(nullptr, 0);
472}

474void SelectionDAGLegalize::LegalizeStoreOps(SDNode *Node) {
475 StoreSDNode *ST = cast<StoreSDNode>(Node);
476 SDValue Chain = ST->getChain();
477 SDValue Ptr = ST->getBasePtr();
478 SDLoc dl(Node);
479
480 unsigned Alignment = ST->getAlignment();
481 MachineMemOperand::Flags MMOFlags = ST->getMemOperand()->getFlags();
482 AAMDNodes AAInfo = ST->getAAInfo();
483
484 if (!ST->isTruncatingStore()) {
485 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Legalizing store operation\n");
486 if (SDNode *OptStore = OptimizeFloatStore(ST).getNode()) {
487 ReplaceNode(ST, OptStore);
488 return;
489 }
490
491 SDValue Value = ST->getValue();
492 MVT VT = Value.getSimpleValueType();
493 switch (TLI.getOperationAction(ISD::STORE, VT)) {
494 default: llvm_unreachable("This action is not supported yet!");
495 case TargetLowering::Legal: {
496 // If this is an unaligned store and the target doesn't support it,
497 // expand it.
498 EVT MemVT = ST->getMemoryVT();
499 const DataLayout &DL = DAG.getDataLayout();
500 if (!TLI.allowsMemoryAccess(*DAG.getContext(), DL, MemVT,
501 *ST->getMemOperand())) {
502 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Expanding unsupported unaligned store\n");
503 SDValue Result = TLI.expandUnalignedStore(ST, DAG);
504 ReplaceNode(SDValue(ST, 0), Result);
505 } else
506 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Legal store\n");
507 break;
508 }
509 case TargetLowering::Custom: {
510 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Trying custom lowering\n");
511 SDValue Res = TLI.LowerOperation(SDValue(Node, 0), DAG);
512 if (Res && Res != SDValue(Node, 0))
513 ReplaceNode(SDValue(Node, 0), Res);
514 return;
515 }
516 case TargetLowering::Promote: {
517 MVT NVT = TLI.getTypeToPromoteTo(ISD::STORE, VT);
518 assert(NVT.getSizeInBits() == VT.getSizeInBits() &&
519 "Can only promote stores to same size type");
520 Value = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, dl, NVT, Value);
521 SDValue Result =
522 DAG.getStore(Chain, dl, Value, Ptr, ST->getPointerInfo(),
523 Alignment, MMOFlags, AAInfo);
524 ReplaceNode(SDValue(Node, 0), Result);
525 break;
526 }
527 }
528 return;
529 }
530
531 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Legalizing truncating store operations\n");
532 SDValue Value = ST->getValue();
533 EVT StVT = ST->getMemoryVT();
534 unsigned StWidth = StVT.getSizeInBits();
535 auto &DL = DAG.getDataLayout();
536
537 if (StWidth != StVT.getStoreSizeInBits()) {
538 // Promote to a byte-sized store with upper bits zero if not
539 // storing an integral number of bytes. For example, promote
540 // TRUNCSTORE:i1 X -> TRUNCSTORE:i8 (and X, 1)
541 EVT NVT = EVT::getIntegerVT(*DAG.getContext(),
542 StVT.getStoreSizeInBits());
543 Value = DAG.getZeroExtendInReg(Value, dl, StVT);
544 SDValue Result =
545 DAG.getTruncStore(Chain, dl, Value, Ptr, ST->getPointerInfo(), NVT,
546 Alignment, MMOFlags, AAInfo);
547 ReplaceNode(SDValue(Node, 0), Result);
548 } else if (StWidth & (StWidth - 1)) {
549 // If not storing a power-of-2 number of bits, expand as two stores.
550 assert(!StVT.isVector() && "Unsupported truncstore!");
551 unsigned LogStWidth = Log2_32(StWidth);
552 assert(LogStWidth < 32);
553 unsigned RoundWidth = 1 << LogStWidth;
554 assert(RoundWidth < StWidth);
555 unsigned ExtraWidth = StWidth - RoundWidth;
556 assert(ExtraWidth < RoundWidth);
557 assert(!(RoundWidth % 8) && !(ExtraWidth % 8) &&
558 "Store size not an integral number of bytes!");
559 EVT RoundVT = EVT::getIntegerVT(*DAG.getContext(), RoundWidth);
560 EVT ExtraVT = EVT::getIntegerVT(*DAG.getContext(), ExtraWidth);
561 SDValue Lo, Hi;
562 unsigned IncrementSize;
563
564 if (DL.isLittleEndian()) {
565 // TRUNCSTORE:i24 X -> TRUNCSTORE:i16 X, TRUNCSTORE@+2:i8 (srl X, 16)
566 // Store the bottom RoundWidth bits.
567 Lo = DAG.getTruncStore(Chain, dl, Value, Ptr, ST->getPointerInfo(),
568 RoundVT, Alignment, MMOFlags, AAInfo);
569
570 // Store the remaining ExtraWidth bits.
571 IncrementSize = RoundWidth / 8;
572 Ptr = DAG.getPointerAdd(dl, Ptr, IncrementSize);
573 Hi = DAG.getNode(
574 ISD::SRL, dl, Value.getValueType(), Value,
575 DAG.getConstant(RoundWidth, dl,
576 TLI.getShiftAmountTy(Value.getValueType(), DL)));
577 Hi = DAG.getTruncStore(
578 Chain, dl, Hi, Ptr,
579 ST->getPointerInfo().getWithOffset(IncrementSize), ExtraVT,
580 MinAlign(Alignment, IncrementSize), MMOFlags, AAInfo);
581 } else {
582 // Big endian - avoid unaligned stores.
583 // TRUNCSTORE:i24 X -> TRUNCSTORE:i16 (srl X, 8), TRUNCSTORE@+2:i8 X
584 // Store the top RoundWidth bits.
585 Hi = DAG.getNode(
586 ISD::SRL, dl, Value.getValueType(), Value,
587 DAG.getConstant(ExtraWidth, dl,
588 TLI.getShiftAmountTy(Value.getValueType(), DL)));
589 Hi = DAG.getTruncStore(Chain, dl, Hi, Ptr, ST->getPointerInfo(),
590 RoundVT, Alignment, MMOFlags, AAInfo);
591
592 // Store the remaining ExtraWidth bits.
593 IncrementSize = RoundWidth / 8;
594 Ptr = DAG.getPointerAdd(dl, Ptr, IncrementSize);
595 Lo = DAG.getTruncStore(
596 Chain, dl, Value, Ptr,
597 ST->getPointerInfo().getWithOffset(IncrementSize), ExtraVT,
598 MinAlign(Alignment, IncrementSize), MMOFlags, AAInfo);
599 }
600
601 // The order of the stores doesn't matter.
602 SDValue Result = DAG.getNode(ISD::TokenFactor, dl, MVT::Other, Lo, Hi);
603 ReplaceNode(SDValue(Node, 0), Result);
604 } else {
605 switch (TLI.getTruncStoreAction(ST->getValue().getValueType(), StVT)) {
606 default: llvm_unreachable("This action is not supported yet!");
607 case TargetLowering::Legal: {
608 EVT MemVT = ST->getMemoryVT();
609 // If this is an unaligned store and the target doesn't support it,
610 // expand it.
611 if (!TLI.allowsMemoryAccess(*DAG.getContext(), DL, MemVT,
612 *ST->getMemOperand())) {
613 SDValue Result = TLI.expandUnalignedStore(ST, DAG);
614 ReplaceNode(SDValue(ST, 0), Result);
615 }
616 break;
617 }
618 case TargetLowering::Custom: {
619 SDValue Res = TLI.LowerOperation(SDValue(Node, 0), DAG);
620 if (Res && Res != SDValue(Node, 0))
621 ReplaceNode(SDValue(Node, 0), Res);
622 return;
623 }
624 case TargetLowering::Expand:
625 assert(!StVT.isVector() &&
626 "Vector Stores are handled in LegalizeVectorOps");
627
628 SDValue Result;
629
630 // TRUNCSTORE:i16 i32 -> STORE i16
631 if (TLI.isTypeLegal(StVT)) {
632 Value = DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, dl, StVT, Value);
633 Result = DAG.getStore(Chain, dl, Value, Ptr, ST->getPointerInfo(),
634 Alignment, MMOFlags, AAInfo);
635 } else {
636 // The in-memory type isn't legal. Truncate to the type it would promote
637 // to, and then do a truncstore.
638 Value = DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, dl,
639 TLI.getTypeToTransformTo(*DAG.getContext(), StVT),
640 Value);
641 Result = DAG.getTruncStore(Chain, dl, Value, Ptr, ST->getPointerInfo(),
642 StVT, Alignment, MMOFlags, AAInfo);
643 }
644
645 ReplaceNode(SDValue(Node, 0), Result);
646 break;
647 }
648 }
649}
650
651void SelectionDAGLegalize::LegalizeLoadOps(SDNode *Node) {
652 LoadSDNode *LD = cast<LoadSDNode>(Node);
653 SDValue Chain = LD->getChain(); // The chain.
654 SDValue Ptr = LD->getBasePtr(); // The base pointer.
655 SDValue Value; // The value returned by the load op.
656 SDLoc dl(Node);
657
658 ISD::LoadExtType ExtType = LD->getExtensionType();
659 if (ExtType == ISD::NON_EXTLOAD) {
660 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Legalizing non-extending load operation\n");
661 MVT VT = Node->getSimpleValueType(0);
662 SDValue RVal = SDValue(Node, 0);
663 SDValue RChain = SDValue(Node, 1);
664
665 switch (TLI.getOperationAction(Node->getOpcode(), VT)) {
666 default: llvm_unreachable("This action is not supported yet!");
667 case TargetLowering::Legal: {
668 EVT MemVT = LD->getMemoryVT();
669 const DataLayout &DL = DAG.getDataLayout();
670 // If this is an unaligned load and the target doesn't support it,
671 // expand it.
672 if (!TLI.allowsMemoryAccess(*DAG.getContext(), DL, MemVT,
673 *LD->getMemOperand())) {
674 std::tie(RVal, RChain) = TLI.expandUnalignedLoad(LD, DAG);
675 }
676 break;
677 }
678 case TargetLowering::Custom:
679 if (SDValue Res = TLI.LowerOperation(RVal, DAG)) {
680 RVal = Res;
681 RChain = Res.getValue(1);
682 }
683 break;
684
685 case TargetLowering::Promote: {
686 MVT NVT = TLI.getTypeToPromoteTo(Node->getOpcode(), VT);
687 assert(NVT.getSizeInBits() == VT.getSizeInBits() &&
688 "Can only promote loads to same size type");
689
690 SDValue Res = DAG.getLoad(NVT, dl, Chain, Ptr, LD->getMemOperand());
691 RVal = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, dl, VT, Res);
692 RChain = Res.getValue(1);
693 break;
694 }
695 }
696 if (RChain.getNode() != Node) {
697 assert(RVal.getNode() != Node && "Load must be completely replaced");
698 DAG.ReplaceAllUsesOfValueWith(SDValue(Node, 0), RVal);
699 DAG.ReplaceAllUsesOfValueWith(SDValue(Node, 1), RChain);
700 if (UpdatedNodes) {
701 UpdatedNodes->insert(RVal.getNode());
702 UpdatedNodes->insert(RChain.getNode());
703 }
704 ReplacedNode(Node);
705 }
706 return;
707 }
708
709 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Legalizing extending load operation\n");
710 EVT SrcVT = LD->getMemoryVT();
711 unsigned SrcWidth = SrcVT.getSizeInBits();
712 unsigned Alignment = LD->getAlignment();
713 MachineMemOperand::Flags MMOFlags = LD->getMemOperand()->getFlags();
714 AAMDNodes AAInfo = LD->getAAInfo();
715
716 if (SrcWidth != SrcVT.getStoreSizeInBits() &&
717 // Some targets pretend to have an i1 loading operation, and actually
718 // load an i8. This trick is correct for ZEXTLOAD because the top 7
719 // bits are guaranteed to be zero; it helps the optimizers understand
720 // that these bits are zero. It is also useful for EXTLOAD, since it
721 // tells the optimizers that those bits are undefined. It would be
722 // nice to have an effective generic way of getting these benefits...
723 // Until such a way is found, don't insist on promoting i1 here.
724 (SrcVT != MVT::i1 ||
725 TLI.getLoadExtAction(ExtType, Node->getValueType(0), MVT::i1) ==
726 TargetLowering::Promote)) {
727 // Promote to a byte-sized load if not loading an integral number of
728 // bytes. For example, promote EXTLOAD:i20 -> EXTLOAD:i24.
729 unsigned NewWidth = SrcVT.getStoreSizeInBits();
730 EVT NVT = EVT::getIntegerVT(*DAG.getContext(), NewWidth);
731 SDValue Ch;
732
733 // The extra bits are guaranteed to be zero, since we stored them that
734 // way. A zext load from NVT thus automatically gives zext from SrcVT.
735
736 ISD::LoadExtType NewExtType =
737 ExtType == ISD::ZEXTLOAD ? ISD::ZEXTLOAD : ISD::EXTLOAD;
738
739 SDValue Result =
740 DAG.getExtLoad(NewExtType, dl, Node->getValueType(0), Chain, Ptr,
741 LD->getPointerInfo(), NVT, Alignment, MMOFlags, AAInfo);
742
743 Ch = Result.getValue(1); // The chain.
744
745 if (ExtType == ISD::SEXTLOAD)
746 // Having the top bits zero doesn't help when sign extending.
747 Result = DAG.getNode(ISD::SIGN_EXTEND_INREG, dl,
748 Result.getValueType(),
749 Result, DAG.getValueType(SrcVT));
750 else if (ExtType == ISD::ZEXTLOAD || NVT == Result.getValueType())
751 // All the top bits are guaranteed to be zero - inform the optimizers.
752 Result = DAG.getNode(ISD::AssertZext, dl,
753 Result.getValueType(), Result,
754 DAG.getValueType(SrcVT));
755
756 Value = Result;
757 Chain = Ch;
758 } else if (SrcWidth & (SrcWidth - 1)) {
759 // If not loading a power-of-2 number of bits, expand as two loads.
760 assert(!SrcVT.isVector() && "Unsupported extload!");
761 unsigned LogSrcWidth = Log2_32(SrcWidth);
762 assert(LogSrcWidth < 32);
763 unsigned RoundWidth = 1 << LogSrcWidth;
764 assert(RoundWidth < SrcWidth);
765 unsigned ExtraWidth = SrcWidth - RoundWidth;
766 assert(ExtraWidth < RoundWidth);
767 assert(!(RoundWidth % 8) && !(ExtraWidth % 8) &&
768 "Load size not an integral number of bytes!");
769 EVT RoundVT = EVT::getIntegerVT(*DAG.getContext(), RoundWidth);
770 EVT ExtraVT = EVT::getIntegerVT(*DAG.getContext(), ExtraWidth);
771 SDValue Lo, Hi, Ch;
772 unsigned IncrementSize;
773 auto &DL = DAG.getDataLayout();
774
775 if (DL.isLittleEndian()) {
776 // EXTLOAD:i24 -> ZEXTLOAD:i16 | (shl EXTLOAD@+2:i8, 16)
777 // Load the bottom RoundWidth bits.
778 Lo = DAG.getExtLoad(ISD::ZEXTLOAD, dl, Node->getValueType(0), Chain, Ptr,
779 LD->getPointerInfo(), RoundVT, Alignment, MMOFlags,
780 AAInfo);
781
782 // Load the remaining ExtraWidth bits.
783 IncrementSize = RoundWidth / 8;
784 Ptr = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, dl, Ptr.getValueType(), Ptr,
785 DAG.getConstant(IncrementSize, dl,
786 Ptr.getValueType()));
787 Hi = DAG.getExtLoad(ExtType, dl, Node->getValueType(0), Chain, Ptr,
788 LD->getPointerInfo().getWithOffset(IncrementSize),
789 ExtraVT, MinAlign(Alignment, IncrementSize), MMOFlags,
790 AAInfo);
791
792 // Build a factor node to remember that this load is independent of
793 // the other one.
794 Ch = DAG.getNode(ISD::TokenFactor, dl, MVT::Other, Lo.getValue(1),
795 Hi.getValue(1));
796
797 // Move the top bits to the right place.
798 Hi = DAG.getNode(
799 ISD::SHL, dl, Hi.getValueType(), Hi,
800 DAG.getConstant(RoundWidth, dl,
801 TLI.getShiftAmountTy(Hi.getValueType(), DL)));
802
803 // Join the hi and lo parts.
804 Value = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, dl, Node->getValueType(0), Lo, Hi);
805 } else {
806 // Big endian - avoid unaligned loads.
807 // EXTLOAD:i24 -> (shl EXTLOAD:i16, 8) | ZEXTLOAD@+2:i8
808 // Load the top RoundWidth bits.
809 Hi = DAG.getExtLoad(ExtType, dl, Node->getValueType(0), Chain, Ptr,
810 LD->getPointerInfo(), RoundVT, Alignment, MMOFlags,
811 AAInfo);
812
813 // Load the remaining ExtraWidth bits.
814 IncrementSize = RoundWidth / 8;
815 Ptr = DAG.getPointerAdd(dl, Ptr, IncrementSize);
816 Lo = DAG.getExtLoad(ISD::ZEXTLOAD, dl, Node->getValueType(0), Chain, Ptr,
817 LD->getPointerInfo().getWithOffset(IncrementSize),
818 ExtraVT, MinAlign(Alignment, IncrementSize), MMOFlags,
819 AAInfo);
820
821 // Build a factor node to remember that this load is independent of
822 // the other one.
823 Ch = DAG.getNode(ISD::TokenFactor, dl, MVT::Other, Lo.getValue(1),
824 Hi.getValue(1));
825
826 // Move the top bits to the right place.
827 Hi = DAG.getNode(
828 ISD::SHL, dl, Hi.getValueType(), Hi,
829 DAG.getConstant(ExtraWidth, dl,
830 TLI.getShiftAmountTy(Hi.getValueType(), DL)));
831
832 // Join the hi and lo parts.
833 Value = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, dl, Node->getValueType(0), Lo, Hi);
834 }
835
836 Chain = Ch;
837 } else {
838 bool isCustom = false;
839 switch (TLI.getLoadExtAction(ExtType, Node->getValueType(0),
840 SrcVT.getSimpleVT())) {
841 default: llvm_unreachable("This action is not supported yet!");
842 case TargetLowering::Custom:
843 isCustom = true;
844 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
845 case TargetLowering::Legal:
846 Value = SDValue(Node, 0);
847 Chain = SDValue(Node, 1);
848
849 if (isCustom) {
850 if (SDValue Res = TLI.LowerOperation(SDValue(Node, 0), DAG)) {
851 Value = Res;
852 Chain = Res.getValue(1);
853 }
854 } else {
855 // If this is an unaligned load and the target doesn't support it,
856 // expand it.
857 EVT MemVT = LD->getMemoryVT();
858 const DataLayout &DL = DAG.getDataLayout();
859 if (!TLI.allowsMemoryAccess(*DAG.getContext(), DL, MemVT,
860 *LD->getMemOperand())) {
861 std::tie(Value, Chain) = TLI.expandUnalignedLoad(LD, DAG);
862 }
863 }
864 break;
865
866 case TargetLowering::Expand: {
867 EVT DestVT = Node->getValueType(0);
868 if (!TLI.isLoadExtLegal(ISD::EXTLOAD, DestVT, SrcVT)) {
869 // If the source type is not legal, see if there is a legal extload to
870 // an intermediate type that we can then extend further.
871 EVT LoadVT = TLI.getRegisterType(SrcVT.getSimpleVT());
872 if (TLI.isTypeLegal(SrcVT) || // Same as SrcVT == LoadVT?
873 TLI.isLoadExtLegal(ExtType, LoadVT, SrcVT)) {
874 // If we are loading a legal type, this is a non-extload followed by a
875 // full extend.
876 ISD::LoadExtType MidExtType =
877 (LoadVT == SrcVT) ? ISD::NON_EXTLOAD : ExtType;
878
879 SDValue Load = DAG.getExtLoad(MidExtType, dl, LoadVT, Chain, Ptr,
880 SrcVT, LD->getMemOperand());
881 unsigned ExtendOp =
882 ISD::getExtForLoadExtType(SrcVT.isFloatingPoint(), ExtType);
883 Value = DAG.getNode(ExtendOp, dl, Node->getValueType(0), Load);
884 Chain = Load.getValue(1);
885 break;
886 }
887
888 // Handle the special case of fp16 extloads. EXTLOAD doesn't have the
889 // normal undefined upper bits behavior to allow using an in-reg extend
890 // with the illegal FP type, so load as an integer and do the
891 // from-integer conversion.
892 if (SrcVT.getScalarType() == MVT::f16) {
893 EVT ISrcVT = SrcVT.changeTypeToInteger();
894 EVT IDestVT = DestVT.changeTypeToInteger();
895 EVT LoadVT = TLI.getRegisterType(IDestVT.getSimpleVT());
896
897 SDValue Result = DAG.getExtLoad(ISD::ZEXTLOAD, dl, LoadVT,
898 Chain, Ptr, ISrcVT,
899 LD->getMemOperand());
900 Value = DAG.getNode(ISD::FP16_TO_FP, dl, DestVT, Result);
901 Chain = Result.getValue(1);
902 break;
903 }
904 }
905
906 assert(!SrcVT.isVector() &&
907 "Vector Loads are handled in LegalizeVectorOps");
908
909 // FIXME: This does not work for vectors on most targets. Sign-
910 // and zero-extend operations are currently folded into extending
911 // loads, whether they are legal or not, and then we end up here
912 // without any support for legalizing them.
913 assert(ExtType != ISD::EXTLOAD &&
914 "EXTLOAD should always be supported!");
915 // Turn the unsupported load into an EXTLOAD followed by an
916 // explicit zero/sign extend inreg.
917 SDValue Result = DAG.getExtLoad(ISD::EXTLOAD, dl,
918 Node->getValueType(0),
919 Chain, Ptr, SrcVT,
920 LD->getMemOperand());
921 SDValue ValRes;
922 if (ExtType == ISD::SEXTLOAD)
923 ValRes = DAG.getNode(ISD::SIGN_EXTEND_INREG, dl,
924 Result.getValueType(),
925 Result, DAG.getValueType(SrcVT));
926 else
927 ValRes = DAG.getZeroExtendInReg(Result, dl, SrcVT.getScalarType());
928 Value = ValRes;
929 Chain = Result.getValue(1);
930 break;
931 }
932 }
933 }
934
935 // Since loads produce two values, make sure to remember that we legalized
936 // both of them.
937 if (Chain.getNode() != Node) {
938 assert(Value.getNode() != Node && "Load must be completely replaced");
939 DAG.ReplaceAllUsesOfValueWith(SDValue(Node, 0), Value);
940 DAG.ReplaceAllUsesOfValueWith(SDValue(Node, 1), Chain);
941 if (UpdatedNodes) {
942 UpdatedNodes->insert(Value.getNode());
943 UpdatedNodes->insert(Chain.getNode());
944 }
945 ReplacedNode(Node);
946 }
947}
948
949/// Return a legal replacement for the given operation, with all legal operands.
950void SelectionDAGLegalize::LegalizeOp(SDNode *Node) {
951 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "\nLegalizing: "; Node->dump(&DAG));
952
953 // Allow illegal target nodes and illegal registers.
954 if (Node->getOpcode() == ISD::TargetConstant ||
955 Node->getOpcode() == ISD::Register)
956 return;
957
958#ifndef NDEBUG
959 for (unsigned i = 0, e = Node->getNumValues(); i != e; ++i)
960 assert((TLI.getTypeAction(*DAG.getContext(), Node->getValueType(i)) ==
961 TargetLowering::TypeLegal ||
962 TLI.isTypeLegal(Node->getValueType(i))) &&
963 "Unexpected illegal type!");
964
965 for (const SDValue &Op : Node->op_values())
966 assert((TLI.getTypeAction(*DAG.getContext(), Op.getValueType()) ==
967 TargetLowering::TypeLegal ||
968 TLI.isTypeLegal(Op.getValueType()) ||
969 Op.getOpcode() == ISD::TargetConstant ||
970 Op.getOpcode() == ISD::Register) &&
971 "Unexpected illegal type!");
972#endif
973
974 // Figure out the correct action; the way to query this varies by opcode
975 TargetLowering::LegalizeAction Action = TargetLowering::Legal;
976 bool SimpleFinishLegalizing = true;
977 switch (Node->getOpcode()) {
978 case ISD::INTRINSIC_W_CHAIN:
979 case ISD::INTRINSIC_WO_CHAIN:
980 case ISD::INTRINSIC_VOID:
981 case ISD::STACKSAVE:
982 Action = TLI.getOperationAction(Node->getOpcode(), MVT::Other);
983 break;
984 case ISD::GET_DYNAMIC_AREA_OFFSET:
985 Action = TLI.getOperationAction(Node->getOpcode(),
986 Node->getValueType(0));
987 break;
988 case ISD::VAARG:
989 Action = TLI.getOperationAction(Node->getOpcode(),
990 Node->getValueType(0));
991 if (Action != TargetLowering::Promote)
992 Action = TLI.getOperationAction(Node->getOpcode(), MVT::Other);
993 break;
994 case ISD::FP_TO_FP16:
995 case ISD::SINT_TO_FP:
996 case ISD::UINT_TO_FP:
997 case ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT:
998 case ISD::LROUND:
999 case ISD::LLROUND:
1000 case ISD::LRINT:
1001 case ISD::LLRINT:
1002 Action = TLI.getOperationAction(Node->getOpcode(),
1003 Node->getOperand(0).getValueType());
1004 break;
1005 case ISD::FP_ROUND_INREG:
1006 case ISD::SIGN_EXTEND_INREG: {
1007 EVT InnerType = cast<VTSDNode>(Node->getOperand(1))->getVT();
1008 Action = TLI.getOperationAction(Node->getOpcode(), InnerType);
1009 break;
1010 }
1011 case ISD::ATOMIC_STORE:
1012 Action = TLI.getOperationAction(Node->getOpcode(),
1013 Node->getOperand(2).getValueType());
1014 break;
1015 case ISD::SELECT_CC:
1016 case ISD::SETCC:
1017 case ISD::BR_CC: {
1018 unsigned CCOperand = Node->getOpcode() == ISD::SELECT_CC ? 4 :
1019 Node->getOpcode() == ISD::SETCC ? 2 : 1;
1020 unsigned CompareOperand = Node->getOpcode() == ISD::BR_CC ? 2 : 0;
1021 MVT OpVT = Node->getOperand(CompareOperand).getSimpleValueType();
1022 ISD::CondCode CCCode =
1023 cast<CondCodeSDNode>(Node->getOperand(CCOperand))->get();
1024 Action = TLI.getCondCodeAction(CCCode, OpVT);
1025 if (Action == TargetLowering::Legal) {
1026 if (Node->getOpcode() == ISD::SELECT_CC)
1027 Action = TLI.getOperationAction(Node->getOpcode(),
1028 Node->getValueType(0));
1029 else
1030 Action = TLI.getOperationAction(Node->getOpcode(), OpVT);
1031 }
1032 break;
1033 }
1034 case ISD::LOAD:
1035 case ISD::STORE:
1036 // FIXME: Model these properly. LOAD and STORE are complicated, and
1037 // STORE expects the unlegalized operand in some cases.
1038 SimpleFinishLegalizing = false;
1039 break;
1040 case ISD::CALLSEQ_START:
1041 case ISD::CALLSEQ_END:
1042 // FIXME: This shouldn't be necessary. These nodes have special properties
1043 // dealing with the recursive nature of legalization. Removing this
1044 // special case should be done as part of making LegalizeDAG non-recursive.
1045 SimpleFinishLegalizing = false;
1046 break;
1047 case ISD::EXTRACT_ELEMENT:
1048 case ISD::FLT_ROUNDS_:
1049 case ISD::MERGE_VALUES:
1050 case ISD::EH_RETURN:
1051 case ISD::FRAME_TO_ARGS_OFFSET:
1052 case ISD::EH_DWARF_CFA:
1053 case ISD::EH_SJLJ_SETJMP:
1054 case ISD::EH_SJLJ_LONGJMP:
1055 case ISD::EH_SJLJ_SETUP_DISPATCH:
1056 // These operations lie about being legal: when they claim to be legal,
1057 // they should actually be expanded.
1058 Action = TLI.getOperationAction(Node->getOpcode(), Node->getValueType(0));
1059 if (Action == TargetLowering::Legal)
1060 Action = TargetLowering::Expand;
1061 break;
1062 case ISD::INIT_TRAMPOLINE:
1063 case ISD::ADJUST_TRAMPOLINE:
1064 case ISD::FRAMEADDR:
1065 case ISD::RETURNADDR:
1066 case ISD::ADDROFRETURNADDR:
1067 case ISD::SPONENTRY:
1068 // These operations lie about being legal: when they claim to be legal,
1069 // they should actually be custom-lowered.
1070 Action = TLI.getOperationAction(Node->getOpcode(), Node->getValueType(0));
1071 if (Action == TargetLowering::Legal)
1072 Action = TargetLowering::Custom;
1073 break;
1074 case ISD::READCYCLECOUNTER:
1075 // READCYCLECOUNTER returns an i64, even if type legalization might have
1076 // expanded that to several smaller types.
1077 Action = TLI.getOperationAction(Node->getOpcode(), MVT::i64);
1078 break;
1079 case ISD::READ_REGISTER:
1080 case ISD::WRITE_REGISTER:
1081 // Named register is legal in the DAG, but blocked by register name
1082 // selection if not implemented by target (to chose the correct register)
1083 // They'll be converted to Copy(To/From)Reg.
1084 Action = TargetLowering::Legal;
1085 break;
1086 case ISD::DEBUGTRAP:
1087 Action = TLI.getOperationAction(Node->getOpcode(), Node->getValueType(0));
1088 if (Action == TargetLowering::Expand) {
1089 // replace ISD::DEBUGTRAP with ISD::TRAP
1090 SDValue NewVal;
1091 NewVal = DAG.getNode(ISD::TRAP, SDLoc(Node), Node->getVTList(),
1092 Node->getOperand(0));
1093 ReplaceNode(Node, NewVal.getNode());
1094 LegalizeOp(NewVal.getNode());
1095 return;
1096 }
1097 break;
1098 case ISD::STRICT_FADD:
1099 case ISD::STRICT_FSUB:
1100 case ISD::STRICT_FMUL:
1101 case ISD::STRICT_FDIV:
1102 case ISD::STRICT_FREM:
1103 case ISD::STRICT_FSQRT:
1104 case ISD::STRICT_FMA:
1105 case ISD::STRICT_FPOW:
1106 case ISD::STRICT_FPOWI:
1107 case ISD::STRICT_FSIN:
1108 case ISD::STRICT_FCOS:
1109 case ISD::STRICT_FEXP:
1110 case ISD::STRICT_FEXP2:
1111 case ISD::STRICT_FLOG:
1112 case ISD::STRICT_FLOG10:
1113 case ISD::STRICT_FLOG2:
1114 case ISD::STRICT_FRINT:
1115 case ISD::STRICT_FNEARBYINT:
1116 case ISD::STRICT_FMAXNUM:
1117 case ISD::STRICT_FMINNUM:
1118 case ISD::STRICT_FCEIL:
1119 case ISD::STRICT_FFLOOR:
1120 case ISD::STRICT_FROUND:
1121 case ISD::STRICT_FTRUNC:
1122 case ISD::STRICT_FP_ROUND:
1123 case ISD::STRICT_FP_EXTEND:
1124 // These pseudo-ops get legalized as if they were their non-strict
1125 // equivalent. For instance, if ISD::FSQRT is legal then ISD::STRICT_FSQRT
1126 // is also legal, but if ISD::FSQRT requires expansion then so does
1127 // ISD::STRICT_FSQRT.
1128 Action = TLI.getStrictFPOperationAction(Node->getOpcode(),
1129 Node->getValueType(0));
1130 break;
1131 case ISD::SADDSAT:
1132 case ISD::UADDSAT:
1133 case ISD::SSUBSAT:
1134 case ISD::USUBSAT: {
1135 Action = TLI.getOperationAction(Node->getOpcode(), Node->getValueType(0));
1136 break;
1137 }
1138 case ISD::SMULFIX:
1139 case ISD::SMULFIXSAT:
1140 case ISD::UMULFIX: {
1141 unsigned Scale = Node->getConstantOperandVal(2);
1142 Action = TLI.getFixedPointOperationAction(Node->getOpcode(),
1143 Node->getValueType(0), Scale);
1144 break;
1145 }
1146 case ISD::MSCATTER:
1147 Action = TLI.getOperationAction(Node->getOpcode(),
1148 cast<MaskedScatterSDNode>(Node)->getValue().getValueType());
1149 break;
1150 case ISD::MSTORE:
1151 Action = TLI.getOperationAction(Node->getOpcode(),
1152 cast<MaskedStoreSDNode>(Node)->getValue().getValueType());
1153 break;
1154 case ISD::VECREDUCE_FADD:
1155 case ISD::VECREDUCE_FMUL:
1156 case ISD::VECREDUCE_ADD:
1157 case ISD::VECREDUCE_MUL:
1158 case ISD::VECREDUCE_AND:
1159 case ISD::VECREDUCE_OR:
1160 case ISD::VECREDUCE_XOR:
1161 case ISD::VECREDUCE_SMAX:
1162 case ISD::VECREDUCE_SMIN:
1163 case ISD::VECREDUCE_UMAX:
1164 case ISD::VECREDUCE_UMIN:
1165 case ISD::VECREDUCE_FMAX:
1166 case ISD::VECREDUCE_FMIN:
1167 Action = TLI.getOperationAction(
1168 Node->getOpcode(), Node->getOperand(0).getValueType());
1169 break;
1170 default:
1171 if (Node->getOpcode() >= ISD::BUILTIN_OP_END) {
1172 Action = TargetLowering::Legal;
1173 } else {
1174 Action = TLI.getOperationAction(Node->getOpcode(), Node->getValueType(0));
1175 }
1176 break;
1177 }
1178
1179 if (SimpleFinishLegalizing) {
1180 SDNode *NewNode = Node;
1181 switch (Node->getOpcode()) {
1182 default: break;
1183 case ISD::SHL:
1184 case ISD::SRL:
1185 case ISD::SRA:
1186 case ISD::ROTL:
1187 case ISD::ROTR: {
1188 // Legalizing shifts/rotates requires adjusting the shift amount
1189 // to the appropriate width.
1190 SDValue Op0 = Node->getOperand(0);
1191 SDValue Op1 = Node->getOperand(1);
1192 if (!Op1.getValueType().isVector()) {
1193 SDValue SAO = DAG.getShiftAmountOperand(Op0.getValueType(), Op1);
1194 // The getShiftAmountOperand() may create a new operand node or
1195 // return the existing one. If new operand is created we need
1196 // to update the parent node.
1197 // Do not try to legalize SAO here! It will be automatically legalized
1198 // in the next round.
1199 if (SAO != Op1)
1200 NewNode = DAG.UpdateNodeOperands(Node, Op0, SAO);
1201 }
1202 }
1203 break;
1204 case ISD::FSHL:
1205 case ISD::FSHR:
1206 case ISD::SRL_PARTS:
1207 case ISD::SRA_PARTS:
1208 case ISD::SHL_PARTS: {
1209 // Legalizing shifts/rotates requires adjusting the shift amount
1210 // to the appropriate width.
1211 SDValue Op0 = Node->getOperand(0);
1212 SDValue Op1 = Node->getOperand(1);
1213 SDValue Op2 = Node->getOperand(2);
1214 if (!Op2.getValueType().isVector()) {
1215 SDValue SAO = DAG.getShiftAmountOperand(Op0.getValueType(), Op2);
1216 // The getShiftAmountOperand() may create a new operand node or
1217 // return the existing one. If new operand is created we need
1218 // to update the parent node.
1219 if (SAO != Op2)
1220 NewNode = DAG.UpdateNodeOperands(Node, Op0, Op1, SAO);
1221 }
1222 break;
1223 }
1224 }
1225
1226 if (NewNode != Node) {
1227 ReplaceNode(Node, NewNode);
1228 Node = NewNode;
1229 }
1230 switch (Action) {
1231 case TargetLowering::Legal:
1232 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Legal node: nothing to do\n");
1233 return;
1234 case TargetLowering::Custom:
1235 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Trying custom legalization\n");
1236 // FIXME: The handling for custom lowering with multiple results is
1237 // a complete mess.
1238 if (SDValue Res = TLI.LowerOperation(SDValue(Node, 0), DAG)) {
1239 if (!(Res.getNode() != Node || Res.getResNo() != 0))
1240 return;
1241
1242 if (Node->getNumValues() == 1) {
1243 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Successfully custom legalized node\n");
1244 // We can just directly replace this node with the lowered value.
1245 ReplaceNode(SDValue(Node, 0), Res);
1246 return;
1247 }
1248
1249 SmallVector<SDValue, 8> ResultVals;
1250 for (unsigned i = 0, e = Node->getNumValues(); i != e; ++i)
1251 ResultVals.push_back(Res.getValue(i));
1252 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Successfully custom legalized node\n");
1253 ReplaceNode(Node, ResultVals.data());
1254 return;
1255 }
1256 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Could not custom legalize node\n");
1257 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
1258 case TargetLowering::Expand:
1259 if (ExpandNode(Node))
1260 return;
1261 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
1262 case TargetLowering::LibCall:
1263 ConvertNodeToLibcall(Node);
1264 return;
1265 case TargetLowering::Promote:
1266 PromoteNode(Node);
1267 return;
1268 }
1269 }
1270
1271 switch (Node->getOpcode()) {
1272 default:
1273#ifndef NDEBUG
1274 dbgs() << "NODE: ";
1275 Node->dump( &DAG);
1276 dbgs() << "\n";
1277#endif
1278 llvm_unreachable("Do not know how to legalize this operator!");
1279
1280 case ISD::CALLSEQ_START:
1281 case ISD::CALLSEQ_END:
1282 break;
1283 case ISD::LOAD:
1284 return LegalizeLoadOps(Node);
1285 case ISD::STORE:
1286 return LegalizeStoreOps(Node);
1287 }
1288}
1289
1290SDValue SelectionDAGLegalize::ExpandExtractFromVectorThroughStack(SDValue Op) {
1291 SDValue Vec = Op.getOperand(0);
1292 SDValue Idx = Op.getOperand(1);
1293 SDLoc dl(Op);
1294
1295 // Before we generate a new store to a temporary stack slot, see if there is
1296 // already one that we can use. There often is because when we scalarize
1297 // vector operations (using SelectionDAG::UnrollVectorOp for example) a whole
1298 // series of EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT nodes are generated, one for each element in
1299 // the vector. If all are expanded here, we don't want one store per vector
1300 // element.
1301
1302 // Caches for hasPredecessorHelper
1303 SmallPtrSet<const SDNode *, 32> Visited;
1304 SmallVector<const SDNode *, 16> Worklist;
1305 Visited.insert(Op.getNode());
1306 Worklist.push_back(Idx.getNode());
1307 SDValue StackPtr, Ch;
1308 for (SDNode::use_iterator UI = Vec.getNode()->use_begin(),
1309 UE = Vec.getNode()->use_end(); UI != UE; ++UI) {
1310 SDNode *User = *UI;
1311 if (StoreSDNode *ST = dyn_cast<StoreSDNode>(User)) {
1312 if (ST->isIndexed() || ST->isTruncatingStore() ||
1313 ST->getValue() != Vec)
1314 continue;
1315
1316 // Make sure that nothing else could have stored into the destination of
1317 // this store.
1318 if (!ST->getChain().reachesChainWithoutSideEffects(DAG.getEntryNode()))
1319 continue;
1320
1321 // If the index is dependent on the store we will introduce a cycle when
1322 // creating the load (the load uses the index, and by replacing the chain
1323 // we will make the index dependent on the load). Also, the store might be
1324 // dependent on the extractelement and introduce a cycle when creating
1325 // the load.
1326 if (SDNode::hasPredecessorHelper(ST, Visited, Worklist) ||
1327 ST->hasPredecessor(Op.getNode()))
1328 continue;
1329
1330 StackPtr = ST->getBasePtr();
1331 Ch = SDValue(ST, 0);
1332 break;
1333 }
1334 }
1335
1336 EVT VecVT = Vec.getValueType();
1337
1338 if (!Ch.getNode()) {
1339 // Store the value to a temporary stack slot, then LOAD the returned part.
1340 StackPtr = DAG.CreateStackTemporary(VecVT);
1341 Ch = DAG.getStore(DAG.getEntryNode(), dl, Vec, StackPtr,
1342 MachinePointerInfo());
1343 }
1344
1345 StackPtr = TLI.getVectorElementPointer(DAG, StackPtr, VecVT, Idx);
1346
1347 SDValue NewLoad;
1348
1349 if (Op.getValueType().isVector())
1350 NewLoad =
1351 DAG.getLoad(Op.getValueType(), dl, Ch, StackPtr, MachinePointerInfo());
1352 else
1353 NewLoad = DAG.getExtLoad(ISD::EXTLOAD, dl, Op.getValueType(), Ch, StackPtr,
1354 MachinePointerInfo(),
1355 VecVT.getVectorElementType());
1356
1357 // Replace the chain going out of the store, by the one out of the load.
1358 DAG.ReplaceAllUsesOfValueWith(Ch, SDValue(NewLoad.getNode(), 1));
1359
1360 // We introduced a cycle though, so update the loads operands, making sure
1361 // to use the original store's chain as an incoming chain.
1362 SmallVector<SDValue, 6> NewLoadOperands(NewLoad->op_begin(),
1363 NewLoad->op_end());
1364 NewLoadOperands[0] = Ch;
1365 NewLoad =
1366 SDValue(DAG.UpdateNodeOperands(NewLoad.getNode(), NewLoadOperands), 0);
1367 return NewLoad;
1368}
1369
1370SDValue SelectionDAGLegalize::ExpandInsertToVectorThroughStack(SDValue Op) {
1371 assert(Op.getValueType().isVector() && "Non-vector insert subvector!");
1372
1373 SDValue Vec = Op.getOperand(0);
1374 SDValue Part = Op.getOperand(1);
1375 SDValue Idx = Op.getOperand(2);
1376 SDLoc dl(Op);
1377
1378 // Store the value to a temporary stack slot, then LOAD the returned part.
1379 EVT VecVT = Vec.getValueType();
1380 SDValue StackPtr = DAG.CreateStackTemporary(VecVT);
1381 int FI = cast<FrameIndexSDNode>(StackPtr.getNode())->getIndex();
1382 MachinePointerInfo PtrInfo =
1383 MachinePointerInfo::getFixedStack(DAG.getMachineFunction(), FI);
1384
1385 // First store the whole vector.
1386 SDValue Ch = DAG.getStore(DAG.getEntryNode(), dl, Vec, StackPtr, PtrInfo);
1387
1388 // Then store the inserted part.
1389 SDValue SubStackPtr = TLI.getVectorElementPointer(DAG, StackPtr, VecVT, Idx);
1390
1391 // Store the subvector.
1392 Ch = DAG.getStore(Ch, dl, Part, SubStackPtr, MachinePointerInfo());
1393
1394 // Finally, load the updated vector.
1395 return DAG.getLoad(Op.getValueType(), dl, Ch, StackPtr, PtrInfo);
1396}
1397
1398SDValue SelectionDAGLegalize::ExpandVectorBuildThroughStack(SDNode* Node) {
1399 // We can't handle this case efficiently. Allocate a sufficiently
1400 // aligned object on the stack, store each element into it, then load
1401 // the result as a vector.
1402 // Create the stack frame object.
1403 EVT VT = Node->getValueType(0);
1404 EVT EltVT = VT.getVectorElementType();
1405 SDLoc dl(Node);
1406 SDValue FIPtr = DAG.CreateStackTemporary(VT);
1407 int FI = cast<FrameIndexSDNode>(FIPtr.getNode())->getIndex();
1408 MachinePointerInfo PtrInfo =
1409 MachinePointerInfo::getFixedStack(DAG.getMachineFunction(), FI);
1410
1411 // Emit a store of each element to the stack slot.
1412 SmallVector<SDValue, 8> Stores;
1413 unsigned TypeByteSize = EltVT.getSizeInBits() / 8;
1414 assert(TypeByteSize > 0 && "Vector element type too small for stack store!");
1415 // Store (in the right endianness) the elements to memory.
1416 for (unsigned i = 0, e = Node->getNumOperands(); i != e; ++i) {
1417 // Ignore undef elements.
1418 if (Node->getOperand(i).isUndef()) continue;
1419
1420 unsigned Offset = TypeByteSize*i;
1421
1422 SDValue Idx = DAG.getConstant(Offset, dl, FIPtr.getValueType());
1423 Idx = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, dl, FIPtr.getValueType(), FIPtr, Idx);
1424
1425 // If the destination vector element type is narrower than the source
1426 // element type, only store the bits necessary.
1427 if (EltVT.bitsLT(Node->getOperand(i).getValueType().getScalarType())) {
1428 Stores.push_back(DAG.getTruncStore(DAG.getEntryNode(), dl,
1429 Node->getOperand(i), Idx,
1430 PtrInfo.getWithOffset(Offset), EltVT));
1431 } else
1432 Stores.push_back(DAG.getStore(DAG.getEntryNode(), dl, Node->getOperand(i),
1433 Idx, PtrInfo.getWithOffset(Offset)));
1434 }
1435
1436 SDValue StoreChain;
1437 if (!Stores.empty()) // Not all undef elements?
1438 StoreChain = DAG.getNode(ISD::TokenFactor, dl, MVT::Other, Stores);
1439 else
1440 StoreChain = DAG.getEntryNode();
1441
1442 // Result is a load from the stack slot.
1443 return DAG.getLoad(VT, dl, StoreChain, FIPtr, PtrInfo);
1444}

1446/// Bitcast a floating-point value to an integer value. Only bitcast the part
1447/// containing the sign bit if the target has no integer value capable of
1448/// holding all bits of the floating-point value.
1449void SelectionDAGLegalize::getSignAsIntValue(FloatSignAsInt &State,
1450 const SDLoc &DL,
1451 SDValue Value) const {
1452 EVT FloatVT = Value.getValueType();
1453 unsigned NumBits = FloatVT.getSizeInBits();
1454 State.FloatVT = FloatVT;
1455 EVT IVT = EVT::getIntegerVT(*DAG.getContext(), NumBits);
1456 // Convert to an integer of the same size.
1457 if (TLI.isTypeLegal(IVT)) {
1458 State.IntValue = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL, IVT, Value);
1459 State.SignMask = APInt::getSignMask(NumBits);
1460 State.SignBit = NumBits - 1;
1461 return;
1462 }
1463
1464 auto &DataLayout = DAG.getDataLayout();
1465 // Store the float to memory, then load the sign part out as an integer.
1466 MVT LoadTy = TLI.getRegisterType(*DAG.getContext(), MVT::i8);
1467 // First create a temporary that is aligned for both the load and store.
1468 SDValue StackPtr = DAG.CreateStackTemporary(FloatVT, LoadTy);
1469 int FI = cast<FrameIndexSDNode>(StackPtr.getNode())->getIndex();
1470 // Then store the float to it.
1471 State.FloatPtr = StackPtr;
1472 MachineFunction &MF = DAG.getMachineFunction();
1473 State.FloatPointerInfo = MachinePointerInfo::getFixedStack(MF, FI);
1474 State.Chain = DAG.getStore(DAG.getEntryNode(), DL, Value, State.FloatPtr,
1475 State.FloatPointerInfo);
1476
1477 SDValue IntPtr;
1478 if (DataLayout.isBigEndian()) {
1479 assert(FloatVT.isByteSized() && "Unsupported floating point type!");
1480 // Load out a legal integer with the same sign bit as the float.
1481 IntPtr = StackPtr;
1482 State.IntPointerInfo = State.FloatPointerInfo;
1483 } else {
1484 // Advance the pointer so that the loaded byte will contain the sign bit.
1485 unsigned ByteOffset = (FloatVT.getSizeInBits() / 8) - 1;
1486 IntPtr = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, DL, StackPtr.getValueType(), StackPtr,
1487 DAG.getConstant(ByteOffset, DL, StackPtr.getValueType()));
1488 State.IntPointerInfo = MachinePointerInfo::getFixedStack(MF, FI,
1489 ByteOffset);
1490 }
1491
1492 State.IntPtr = IntPtr;
1493 State.IntValue = DAG.getExtLoad(ISD::EXTLOAD, DL, LoadTy, State.Chain, IntPtr,
1494 State.IntPointerInfo, MVT::i8);
1495 State.SignMask = APInt::getOneBitSet(LoadTy.getSizeInBits(), 7);
1496 State.SignBit = 7;
1497}
1498
1499/// Replace the integer value produced by getSignAsIntValue() with a new value
1500/// and cast the result back to a floating-point type.
1501SDValue SelectionDAGLegalize::modifySignAsInt(const FloatSignAsInt &State,
1502 const SDLoc &DL,
1503 SDValue NewIntValue) const {
1504 if (!State.Chain)
1505 return DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL, State.FloatVT, NewIntValue);
1506
1507 // Override the part containing the sign bit in the value stored on the stack.
1508 SDValue Chain = DAG.getTruncStore(State.Chain, DL, NewIntValue, State.IntPtr,
1509 State.IntPointerInfo, MVT::i8);
1510 return DAG.getLoad(State.FloatVT, DL, Chain, State.FloatPtr,
1511 State.FloatPointerInfo);
1512}
1513
1514SDValue SelectionDAGLegalize::ExpandFCOPYSIGN(SDNode *Node) const {
1515 SDLoc DL(Node);
1516 SDValue Mag = Node->getOperand(0);
1517 SDValue Sign = Node->getOperand(1);
1518
1519 // Get sign bit into an integer value.
1520 FloatSignAsInt SignAsInt;
1521 getSignAsIntValue(SignAsInt, DL, Sign);
1522
1523 EVT IntVT = SignAsInt.IntValue.getValueType();
1524 SDValue SignMask = DAG.getConstant(SignAsInt.SignMask, DL, IntVT);
1525 SDValue SignBit = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, DL, IntVT, SignAsInt.IntValue,
1526 SignMask);
1527
1528 // If FABS is legal transform FCOPYSIGN(x, y) => sign(x) ? -FABS(x) : FABS(X)
1529 EVT FloatVT = Mag.getValueType();
1530 if (TLI.isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::FABS, FloatVT) &&
1531 TLI.isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::FNEG, FloatVT)) {
1532 SDValue AbsValue = DAG.getNode(ISD::FABS, DL, FloatVT, Mag);
1533 SDValue NegValue = DAG.getNode(ISD::FNEG, DL, FloatVT, AbsValue);
1534 SDValue Cond = DAG.getSetCC(DL, getSetCCResultType(IntVT), SignBit,
1535 DAG.getConstant(0, DL, IntVT), ISD::SETNE);
1536 return DAG.getSelect(DL, FloatVT, Cond, NegValue, AbsValue);
1537 }
1538
1539 // Transform Mag value to integer, and clear the sign bit.
1540 FloatSignAsInt MagAsInt;
1541 getSignAsIntValue(MagAsInt, DL, Mag);
1542 EVT MagVT = MagAsInt.IntValue.getValueType();
1543 SDValue ClearSignMask = DAG.getConstant(~MagAsInt.SignMask, DL, MagVT);
1544 SDValue ClearedSign = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, DL, MagVT, MagAsInt.IntValue,
1545 ClearSignMask);
1546
1547 // Get the signbit at the right position for MagAsInt.
1548 int ShiftAmount = SignAsInt.SignBit - MagAsInt.SignBit;
1549 EVT ShiftVT = IntVT;
1550 if (SignBit.getValueSizeInBits() < ClearedSign.getValueSizeInBits()) {
1551 SignBit = DAG.getNode(ISD::ZERO_EXTEND, DL, MagVT, SignBit);
1552 ShiftVT = MagVT;
1553 }
1554 if (ShiftAmount > 0) {
1555 SDValue ShiftCnst = DAG.getConstant(ShiftAmount, DL, ShiftVT);
1556 SignBit = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, DL, ShiftVT, SignBit, ShiftCnst);
1557 } else if (ShiftAmount < 0) {
1558 SDValue ShiftCnst = DAG.getConstant(-ShiftAmount, DL, ShiftVT);
1559 SignBit = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, DL, ShiftVT, SignBit, ShiftCnst);
1560 }
1561 if (SignBit.getValueSizeInBits() > ClearedSign.getValueSizeInBits()) {
1562 SignBit = DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, DL, MagVT, SignBit);
1563 }
1564
1565 // Store the part with the modified sign and convert back to float.
1566 SDValue CopiedSign = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, DL, MagVT, ClearedSign, SignBit);
1567 return modifySignAsInt(MagAsInt, DL, CopiedSign);
1568}
1569
1570SDValue SelectionDAGLegalize::ExpandFABS(SDNode *Node) const {
1571 SDLoc DL(Node);
1572 SDValue Value = Node->getOperand(0);
1573
1574 // Transform FABS(x) => FCOPYSIGN(x, 0.0) if FCOPYSIGN is legal.
1575 EVT FloatVT = Value.getValueType();
1576 if (TLI.isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::FCOPYSIGN, FloatVT)) {
1577 SDValue Zero = DAG.getConstantFP(0.0, DL, FloatVT);
1578 return DAG.getNode(ISD::FCOPYSIGN, DL, FloatVT, Value, Zero);
1579 }
1580
1581 // Transform value to integer, clear the sign bit and transform back.
1582 FloatSignAsInt ValueAsInt;
1583 getSignAsIntValue(ValueAsInt, DL, Value);
1584 EVT IntVT = ValueAsInt.IntValue.getValueType();
1585 SDValue ClearSignMask = DAG.getConstant(~ValueAsInt.SignMask, DL, IntVT);
1586 SDValue ClearedSign = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, DL, IntVT, ValueAsInt.IntValue,
1587 ClearSignMask);
1588 return modifySignAsInt(ValueAsInt, DL, ClearedSign);
1589}
1590
1591void SelectionDAGLegalize::ExpandDYNAMIC_STACKALLOC(SDNode* Node,
1592 SmallVectorImpl<SDValue> &Results) {
1593 unsigned SPReg = TLI.getStackPointerRegisterToSaveRestore();
1594 assert(SPReg && "Target cannot require DYNAMIC_STACKALLOC expansion and"
1595 " not tell us which reg is the stack pointer!");
1596 SDLoc dl(Node);
1597 EVT VT = Node->getValueType(0);
1598 SDValue Tmp1 = SDValue(Node, 0);
1599 SDValue Tmp2 = SDValue(Node, 1);
1600 SDValue Tmp3 = Node->getOperand(2);
1601 SDValue Chain = Tmp1.getOperand(0);
1602
1603 // Chain the dynamic stack allocation so that it doesn't modify the stack
1604 // pointer when other instructions are using the stack.
1605 Chain = DAG.getCALLSEQ_START(Chain, 0, 0, dl);
1606
1607 SDValue Size = Tmp2.getOperand(1);
1608 SDValue SP = DAG.getCopyFromReg(Chain, dl, SPReg, VT);
1609 SDValue SPRegVal = SP;
1610 Chain = SP.getValue(1);
1611 auto IntPtrTy = VT;
1612 if (VT.isFatPointer()) {
1613 IntPtrTy = TLI.getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout(), 0);
1614 SDValue GetOffset = DAG.getTargetConstant(Intrinsic::cheri_cap_offset_get,
1615 dl, IntPtrTy);
1616 SP =
1617 DAG.getNode(ISD::INTRINSIC_WO_CHAIN, dl, IntPtrTy , GetOffset, SPRegVal);
1618 }
1619 unsigned Align = cast<ConstantSDNode>(Tmp3)->getZExtValue();
1620 unsigned StackAlign =
1621 DAG.getSubtarget().getFrameLowering()->getStackAlignment();
1622 Tmp1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::SUB, dl, IntPtrTy, SP, Size); // Value
1623 if (Align > StackAlign)
1624 Tmp1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, IntPtrTy, Tmp1,
1625 DAG.getConstant(-(uint64_t)Align, dl, IntPtrTy));
1626 if (VT.isFatPointer()) {
1627 SDValue SetOffset = DAG.getTargetConstant(Intrinsic::cheri_cap_offset_set,
1628 dl, IntPtrTy);
1629 SDValue SetBounds = DAG.getTargetConstant(Intrinsic::cheri_cap_bounds_set,
1630 dl, IntPtrTy);
1631 Tmp1 =
1632 DAG.getNode(ISD::INTRINSIC_WO_CHAIN, dl, VT.getSimpleVT(), SetOffset, SPRegVal, Tmp1);
1633 // Move the stack pointer *before* setting the bounds!
1634 Chain = DAG.getCopyToReg(Chain, dl, SPReg, Tmp1); // Output chain
1635 Tmp1 =
1636 DAG.getNode(ISD::INTRINSIC_WO_CHAIN, dl, VT.getSimpleVT(), SetBounds, Tmp1, Size);
1637 if (cheri::ShouldCollectCSetBoundsStats) {
1638 llvm::Optional<uint64_t> KnownSize = None;
1639 if (auto CSDN = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(Size)) {
1640 KnownSize = CSDN->getZExtValue();
1641 }
1642 cheri::CSetBoundsStats->add(Align, KnownSize, "ExpandDYNAMIC_STACKALLOC", cheri::SetBoundsPointerSource::Stack,
1643 "", cheri::inferSourceLocation(Node->getDebugLoc(), DAG.getMachineFunction().getName()));
1644 }
1645 } else {
1646 Chain = DAG.getCopyToReg(Chain, dl, SPReg, Tmp1); // Output chain
1647 }
1648
1649 Tmp2 = DAG.getCALLSEQ_END(Chain, DAG.getIntPtrConstant(0, dl, true),
1650 DAG.getIntPtrConstant(0, dl, true), SDValue(), dl);
1651
1652 Results.push_back(Tmp1);
1653 Results.push_back(Tmp2);
1654}
1655
1656/// Legalize a SETCC with given LHS and RHS and condition code CC on the current
1657/// target.
1658///
1659/// If the SETCC has been legalized using AND / OR, then the legalized node
1660/// will be stored in LHS. RHS and CC will be set to SDValue(). NeedInvert
1661/// will be set to false.
1662///
1663/// If the SETCC has been legalized by using getSetCCSwappedOperands(),
1664/// then the values of LHS and RHS will be swapped, CC will be set to the
1665/// new condition, and NeedInvert will be set to false.
1666///
1667/// If the SETCC has been legalized using the inverse condcode, then LHS and
1668/// RHS will be unchanged, CC will set to the inverted condcode, and NeedInvert
1669/// will be set to true. The caller must invert the result of the SETCC with
1670/// SelectionDAG::getLogicalNOT() or take equivalent action to swap the effect
1671/// of a true/false result.
1672///
1673/// \returns true if the SetCC has been legalized, false if it hasn't.
1674bool SelectionDAGLegalize::LegalizeSetCCCondCode(EVT VT, SDValue &LHS,
1675 SDValue &RHS, SDValue &CC,
1676 bool &NeedInvert,
1677 const SDLoc &dl) {
1678 MVT OpVT = LHS.getSimpleValueType();
1679 ISD::CondCode CCCode = cast<CondCodeSDNode>(CC)->get();
1680 NeedInvert = false;
1681 bool NeedSwap = false;
1682 switch (TLI.getCondCodeAction(CCCode, OpVT)) {
1683 default: llvm_unreachable("Unknown condition code action!");
1684 case TargetLowering::Legal:
1685 // Nothing to do.
1686 break;
1687 case TargetLowering::Expand: {
1688 ISD::CondCode InvCC = ISD::getSetCCSwappedOperands(CCCode);
1689 if (TLI.isCondCodeLegalOrCustom(InvCC, OpVT)) {
1690 std::swap(LHS, RHS);
1691 CC = DAG.getCondCode(InvCC);
1692 return true;
1693 }
1694 // Swapping operands didn't work. Try inverting the condition.
1695 InvCC = getSetCCInverse(CCCode, OpVT);
1696 if (!TLI.isCondCodeLegalOrCustom(InvCC, OpVT)) {
1697 // If inverting the condition is not enough, try swapping operands
1698 // on top of it.
1699 InvCC = ISD::getSetCCSwappedOperands(InvCC);
1700 NeedSwap = true;
1701 }
1702 if (TLI.isCondCodeLegalOrCustom(InvCC, OpVT)) {
1703 CC = DAG.getCondCode(InvCC);
1704 NeedInvert = true;
1705 if (NeedSwap)
1706 std::swap(LHS, RHS);
1707 return true;
1708 }
1709
1710 ISD::CondCode CC1 = ISD::SETCC_INVALID, CC2 = ISD::SETCC_INVALID;
1711 unsigned Opc = 0;
1712 switch (CCCode) {
1713 default: llvm_unreachable("Don't know how to expand this condition!");
1714 case ISD::SETO:
1715 assert(TLI.isCondCodeLegal(ISD::SETOEQ, OpVT)
1716 && "If SETO is expanded, SETOEQ must be legal!");
1717 CC1 = ISD::SETOEQ; CC2 = ISD::SETOEQ; Opc = ISD::AND; break;
1718 case ISD::SETUO:
1719 assert(TLI.isCondCodeLegal(ISD::SETUNE, OpVT)
1720 && "If SETUO is expanded, SETUNE must be legal!");
1721 CC1 = ISD::SETUNE; CC2 = ISD::SETUNE; Opc = ISD::OR; break;
1722 case ISD::SETOEQ:
1723 case ISD::SETOGT:
1724 case ISD::SETOGE:
1725 case ISD::SETOLT:
1726 case ISD::SETOLE:
1727 case ISD::SETONE:
1728 case ISD::SETUEQ:
1729 case ISD::SETUNE:
1730 case ISD::SETUGT:
1731 case ISD::SETUGE:
1732 case ISD::SETULT:
1733 case ISD::SETULE:
1734 // If we are floating point, assign and break, otherwise fall through.
1735 if (!OpVT.isInteger()) {
1736 // We can use the 4th bit to tell if we are the unordered
1737 // or ordered version of the opcode.
1738 CC2 = ((unsigned)CCCode & 0x8U) ? ISD::SETUO : ISD::SETO;
1739 Opc = ((unsigned)CCCode & 0x8U) ? ISD::OR : ISD::AND;
1740 CC1 = (ISD::CondCode)(((int)CCCode & 0x7) | 0x10);
1741 break;
1742 }
1743 // Fallthrough if we are unsigned integer.
1744 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
1745 case ISD::SETLE:
1746 case ISD::SETGT:
1747 case ISD::SETGE:
1748 case ISD::SETLT:
1749 case ISD::SETNE:
1750 case ISD::SETEQ:
1751 // If all combinations of inverting the condition and swapping operands
1752 // didn't work then we have no means to expand the condition.
1753 llvm_unreachable("Don't know how to expand this condition!");
1754 }
1755
1756 SDValue SetCC1, SetCC2;
1757 if (CCCode != ISD::SETO && CCCode != ISD::SETUO) {
1758 // If we aren't the ordered or unorder operation,
1759 // then the pattern is (LHS CC1 RHS) Opc (LHS CC2 RHS).
1760 SetCC1 = DAG.getSetCC(dl, VT, LHS, RHS, CC1);
1761 SetCC2 = DAG.getSetCC(dl, VT, LHS, RHS, CC2);
1762 } else {
1763 // Otherwise, the pattern is (LHS CC1 LHS) Opc (RHS CC2 RHS)
1764 SetCC1 = DAG.getSetCC(dl, VT, LHS, LHS, CC1);
1765 SetCC2 = DAG.getSetCC(dl, VT, RHS, RHS, CC2);
1766 }
1767 LHS = DAG.getNode(Opc, dl, VT, SetCC1, SetCC2);
1768 RHS = SDValue();
1769 CC = SDValue();
1770 return true;
1771 }
1772 }
1773 return false;
1774}
1775
1776/// Emit a store/load combination to the stack. This stores
1777/// SrcOp to a stack slot of type SlotVT, truncating it if needed. It then does
1778/// a load from the stack slot to DestVT, extending it if needed.
1779/// The resultant code need not be legal.
1780SDValue SelectionDAGLegalize::EmitStackConvert(SDValue SrcOp, EVT SlotVT,
1781 EVT DestVT, const SDLoc &dl) {
1782 return EmitStackConvert(SrcOp, SlotVT, DestVT, dl, DAG.getEntryNode());
1783}
1784
1785SDValue SelectionDAGLegalize::EmitStackConvert(SDValue SrcOp, EVT SlotVT,
1786 EVT DestVT, const SDLoc &dl,
1787 SDValue Chain) {
1788 // Create the stack frame object.
1789 unsigned SrcAlign = DAG.getDataLayout().getPrefTypeAlignment(
1790 SrcOp.getValueType().getTypeForEVT(*DAG.getContext()));
1791 SDValue FIPtr = DAG.CreateStackTemporary(SlotVT, SrcAlign);
1792
1793 FrameIndexSDNode *StackPtrFI = cast<FrameIndexSDNode>(FIPtr);
1794 int SPFI = StackPtrFI->getIndex();
1795 MachinePointerInfo PtrInfo =
1796 MachinePointerInfo::getFixedStack(DAG.getMachineFunction(), SPFI);
1797
1798 unsigned SrcSize = SrcOp.getValueSizeInBits();
1799 unsigned SlotSize = SlotVT.getSizeInBits();
1800 unsigned DestSize = DestVT.getSizeInBits();
1801 Type *DestType = DestVT.getTypeForEVT(*DAG.getContext());
1802 unsigned DestAlign = DAG.getDataLayout().getPrefTypeAlignment(DestType);
1803
1804 // Emit a store to the stack slot. Use a truncstore if the input value is
1805 // later than DestVT.
1806 SDValue Store;
1807
1808 if (SrcSize > SlotSize)
1809 Store = DAG.getTruncStore(Chain, dl, SrcOp, FIPtr, PtrInfo,
1810 SlotVT, SrcAlign);
1811 else {
1812 assert(SrcSize == SlotSize && "Invalid store");
1813 Store =
1814 DAG.getStore(Chain, dl, SrcOp, FIPtr, PtrInfo, SrcAlign);
1815 }
1816
1817 // Result is a load from the stack slot.
1818 if (SlotSize == DestSize)
1819 return DAG.getLoad(DestVT, dl, Store, FIPtr, PtrInfo, DestAlign);
1820
1821 assert(SlotSize < DestSize && "Unknown extension!");
1822 return DAG.getExtLoad(ISD::EXTLOAD, dl, DestVT, Store, FIPtr, PtrInfo, SlotVT,
1823 DestAlign);
1824}
1825
1826SDValue SelectionDAGLegalize::ExpandSCALAR_TO_VECTOR(SDNode *Node) {
1827 SDLoc dl(Node);
1828 // Create a vector sized/aligned stack slot, store the value to element #0,
1829 // then load the whole vector back out.
1830 SDValue StackPtr = DAG.CreateStackTemporary(Node->getValueType(0));
1831
1832 FrameIndexSDNode *StackPtrFI = cast<FrameIndexSDNode>(StackPtr);
1833 int SPFI = StackPtrFI->getIndex();
1834
1835 SDValue Ch = DAG.getTruncStore(
1836 DAG.getEntryNode(), dl, Node->getOperand(0), StackPtr,
1837 MachinePointerInfo::getFixedStack(DAG.getMachineFunction(), SPFI),
1838 Node->getValueType(0).getVectorElementType());
1839 return DAG.getLoad(
1840 Node->getValueType(0), dl, Ch, StackPtr,
1841 MachinePointerInfo::getFixedStack(DAG.getMachineFunction(), SPFI));
1842}
1843
1844static bool
1845ExpandBVWithShuffles(SDNode *Node, SelectionDAG &DAG,
1846 const TargetLowering &TLI, SDValue &Res) {
1847 unsigned NumElems = Node->getNumOperands();
1848 SDLoc dl(Node);
1849 EVT VT = Node->getValueType(0);
1850
1851 // Try to group the scalars into pairs, shuffle the pairs together, then
1852 // shuffle the pairs of pairs together, etc. until the vector has
1853 // been built. This will work only if all of the necessary shuffle masks
1854 // are legal.
1855
1856 // We do this in two phases; first to check the legality of the shuffles,
1857 // and next, assuming that all shuffles are legal, to create the new nodes.
1858 for (int Phase = 0; Phase < 2; ++Phase) {
1859 SmallVector<std::pair<SDValue, SmallVector<int, 16>>, 16> IntermedVals,
1860 NewIntermedVals;
1861 for (unsigned i = 0; i < NumElems; ++i) {
1862 SDValue V = Node->getOperand(i);
1863 if (V.isUndef())
1864 continue;
1865
1866 SDValue Vec;
1867 if (Phase)
1868 Vec = DAG.getNode(ISD::SCALAR_TO_VECTOR, dl, VT, V);
1869 IntermedVals.push_back(std::make_pair(Vec, SmallVector<int, 16>(1, i)));
1870 }
1871
1872 while (IntermedVals.size() > 2) {
1873 NewIntermedVals.clear();
1874 for (unsigned i = 0, e = (IntermedVals.size() & ~1u); i < e; i += 2) {
1875 // This vector and the next vector are shuffled together (simply to
1876 // append the one to the other).
1877 SmallVector<int, 16> ShuffleVec(NumElems, -1);
1878
1879 SmallVector<int, 16> FinalIndices;
1880 FinalIndices.reserve(IntermedVals[i].second.size() +
1881 IntermedVals[i+1].second.size());
1882
1883 int k = 0;
1884 for (unsigned j = 0, f = IntermedVals[i].second.size(); j != f;
1885 ++j, ++k) {
1886 ShuffleVec[k] = j;
1887 FinalIndices.push_back(IntermedVals[i].second[j]);
1888 }
1889 for (unsigned j = 0, f = IntermedVals[i+1].second.size(); j != f;
1890 ++j, ++k) {
1891 ShuffleVec[k] = NumElems + j;
1892 FinalIndices.push_back(IntermedVals[i+1].second[j]);
1893 }
1894
1895 SDValue Shuffle;
1896 if (Phase)
1897 Shuffle = DAG.getVectorShuffle(VT, dl, IntermedVals[i].first,
1898 IntermedVals[i+1].first,
1899 ShuffleVec);
1900 else if (!TLI.isShuffleMaskLegal(ShuffleVec, VT))
1901 return false;
1902 NewIntermedVals.push_back(
1903 std::make_pair(Shuffle, std::move(FinalIndices)));
1904 }
1905
1906 // If we had an odd number of defined values, then append the last
1907 // element to the array of new vectors.
1908 if ((IntermedVals.size() & 1) != 0)
1909 NewIntermedVals.push_back(IntermedVals.back());
1910
1911 IntermedVals.swap(NewIntermedVals);
1912 }
1913
1914 assert(IntermedVals.size() <= 2 && IntermedVals.size() > 0 &&
1915 "Invalid number of intermediate vectors");
1916 SDValue Vec1 = IntermedVals[0].first;
1917 SDValue Vec2;
1918 if (IntermedVals.size() > 1)
1919 Vec2 = IntermedVals[1].first;
1920 else if (Phase)
1921 Vec2 = DAG.getUNDEF(VT);
1922
1923 SmallVector<int, 16> ShuffleVec(NumElems, -1);
1924 for (unsigned i = 0, e = IntermedVals[0].second.size(); i != e; ++i)
1925 ShuffleVec[IntermedVals[0].second[i]] = i;
1926 for (unsigned i = 0, e = IntermedVals[1].second.size(); i != e; ++i)
1927 ShuffleVec[IntermedVals[1].second[i]] = NumElems + i;
1928
1929 if (Phase)
1930 Res = DAG.getVectorShuffle(VT, dl, Vec1, Vec2, ShuffleVec);
1931 else if (!TLI.isShuffleMaskLegal(ShuffleVec, VT))
1932 return false;
1933 }
1934
1935 return true;
1936}
1937
1938/// Expand a BUILD_VECTOR node on targets that don't
1939/// support the operation, but do support the resultant vector type.
1940SDValue SelectionDAGLegalize::ExpandBUILD_VECTOR(SDNode *Node) {
1941 unsigned NumElems = Node->getNumOperands();
1942 SDValue Value1, Value2;
1943 SDLoc dl(Node);
1944 EVT VT = Node->getValueType(0);
1945 EVT OpVT = Node->getOperand(0).getValueType();
1946 EVT EltVT = VT.getVectorElementType();
1947
1948 // If the only non-undef value is the low element, turn this into a
1949 // SCALAR_TO_VECTOR node. If this is { X, X, X, X }, determine X.
1950 bool isOnlyLowElement = true;
1951 bool MoreThanTwoValues = false;
1952 bool isConstant = true;
1953 for (unsigned i = 0; i < NumElems; ++i) {
1954 SDValue V = Node->getOperand(i);
1955 if (V.isUndef())
1956 continue;
1957 if (i > 0)
1958 isOnlyLowElement = false;
1959 if (!isa<ConstantFPSDNode>(V) && !isa<ConstantSDNode>(V))
1960 isConstant = false;
1961
1962 if (!Value1.getNode()) {
1963 Value1 = V;
1964 } else if (!Value2.getNode()) {
1965 if (V != Value1)
1966 Value2 = V;
1967 } else if (V != Value1 && V != Value2) {
1968 MoreThanTwoValues = true;
1969 }
1970 }
1971
1972 if (!Value1.getNode())
1973 return DAG.getUNDEF(VT);
1974
1975 if (isOnlyLowElement)
1976 return DAG.getNode(ISD::SCALAR_TO_VECTOR, dl, VT, Node->getOperand(0));
1977
1978 // If all elements are constants, create a load from the constant pool.
1979 if (isConstant) {
1980 SmallVector<Constant*, 16> CV;
1981 for (unsigned i = 0, e = NumElems; i != e; ++i) {
1982 if (ConstantFPSDNode *V =
1983 dyn_cast<ConstantFPSDNode>(Node->getOperand(i))) {
1984 CV.push_back(const_cast<ConstantFP *>(V->getConstantFPValue()));
1985 } else if (ConstantSDNode *V =
1986 dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(Node->getOperand(i))) {
1987 if (OpVT==EltVT)
1988 CV.push_back(const_cast<ConstantInt *>(V->getConstantIntValue()));
1989 else {
1990 // If OpVT and EltVT don't match, EltVT is not legal and the
1991 // element values have been promoted/truncated earlier. Undo this;
1992 // we don't want a v16i8 to become a v16i32 for example.
1993 const ConstantInt *CI = V->getConstantIntValue();
1994 CV.push_back(ConstantInt::get(EltVT.getTypeForEVT(*DAG.getContext()),
1995 CI->getZExtValue()));
1996 }
1997 } else {
1998 assert(Node->getOperand(i).isUndef());
1999 Type *OpNTy = EltVT.getTypeForEVT(*DAG.getContext());
2000 CV.push_back(UndefValue::get(OpNTy));
2001 }
2002 }
2003 Constant *CP = ConstantVector::get(CV);
2004 SDValue CPIdx = DAG.getConstantPool(
2005 CP, TLI.getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout(),
2006 DAG.getDataLayout().getGlobalsAddressSpace()));
2007 unsigned Alignment = cast<ConstantPoolSDNode>(CPIdx)->getAlignment();
2008 return DAG.getLoad(
2009 VT, dl, DAG.getEntryNode(), CPIdx,
2010 MachinePointerInfo::getConstantPool(DAG.getMachineFunction()),
2011 Alignment);
2012 }
2013
2014 SmallSet<SDValue, 16> DefinedValues;
2015 for (unsigned i = 0; i < NumElems; ++i) {
2016 if (Node->getOperand(i).isUndef())
2017 continue;
2018 DefinedValues.insert(Node->getOperand(i));
2019 }
2020
2021 if (TLI.shouldExpandBuildVectorWithShuffles(VT, DefinedValues.size())) {
2022 if (!MoreThanTwoValues) {
2023 SmallVector<int, 8> ShuffleVec(NumElems, -1);
2024 for (unsigned i = 0; i < NumElems; ++i) {
2025 SDValue V = Node->getOperand(i);
2026 if (V.isUndef())
2027 continue;
2028 ShuffleVec[i] = V == Value1 ? 0 : NumElems;
2029 }
2030 if (TLI.isShuffleMaskLegal(ShuffleVec, Node->getValueType(0))) {
2031 // Get the splatted value into the low element of a vector register.
2032 SDValue Vec1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::SCALAR_TO_VECTOR, dl, VT, Value1);
2033 SDValue Vec2;
2034 if (Value2.getNode())
2035 Vec2 = DAG.getNode(ISD::SCALAR_TO_VECTOR, dl, VT, Value2);
2036 else
2037 Vec2 = DAG.getUNDEF(VT);
2038
2039 // Return shuffle(LowValVec, undef, <0,0,0,0>)
2040 return DAG.getVectorShuffle(VT, dl, Vec1, Vec2, ShuffleVec);
2041 }
2042 } else {
2043 SDValue Res;
2044 if (ExpandBVWithShuffles(Node, DAG, TLI, Res))
2045 return Res;
2046 }
2047 }
2048
2049 // Otherwise, we can't handle this case efficiently.
2050 return ExpandVectorBuildThroughStack(Node);
2051}
2052
2053// Expand a node into a call to a libcall. If the result value
2054// does not fit into a register, return the lo part and set the hi part to the
2055// by-reg argument. If it does fit into a single register, return the result
2056// and leave the Hi part unset.
2057SDValue SelectionDAGLegalize::ExpandLibCall(RTLIB::Libcall LC, SDNode *Node,
2058 bool isSigned) {
2059 TargetLowering::ArgListTy Args;
2060 TargetLowering::ArgListEntry Entry;
2061 for (const SDValue &Op : Node->op_values()) {
2062 EVT ArgVT = Op.getValueType();
2063 Type *ArgTy = ArgVT.getTypeForEVT(*DAG.getContext());
2064 Entry.Node = Op;
2065 Entry.Ty = ArgTy;
2066 Entry.IsSExt = TLI.shouldSignExtendTypeInLibCall(ArgVT, isSigned);
2067 Entry.IsZExt = !TLI.shouldSignExtendTypeInLibCall(ArgVT, isSigned);
2068 Args.push_back(Entry);
2069 }
2070 SDValue Callee = DAG.getExternalFunctionSymbol(TLI.getLibcallName(LC));
2071
2072 EVT RetVT = Node->getValueType(0);
2073 Type *RetTy = RetVT.getTypeForEVT(*DAG.getContext());
2074
2075 // By default, the input chain to this libcall is the entry node of the
2076 // function. If the libcall is going to be emitted as a tail call then
2077 // TLI.isUsedByReturnOnly will change it to the right chain if the return
2078 // node which is being folded has a non-entry input chain.
2079 SDValue InChain = DAG.getEntryNode();
2080
2081 // isTailCall may be true since the callee does not reference caller stack
2082 // frame. Check if it's in the right position and that the return types match.
2083 SDValue TCChain = InChain;
2084 const Function &F = DAG.getMachineFunction().getFunction();
2085 bool isTailCall =
2086 TLI.isInTailCallPosition(DAG, Node, TCChain) &&
2087 (RetTy == F.getReturnType() || F.getReturnType()->isVoidTy());
2088 if (isTailCall)
2089 InChain = TCChain;
2090
2091 TargetLowering::CallLoweringInfo CLI(DAG);
2092 bool signExtend = TLI.shouldSignExtendTypeInLibCall(RetVT, isSigned);
2093 CLI.setDebugLoc(SDLoc(Node))
2094 .setChain(InChain)
2095 .setLibCallee(TLI.getLibcallCallingConv(LC), RetTy, Callee,
2096 std::move(Args))
2097 .setTailCall(isTailCall)
2098 .setSExtResult(signExtend)
2099 .setZExtResult(!signExtend)
2100 .setIsPostTypeLegalization(true);
2101
2102 std::pair<SDValue, SDValue> CallInfo = TLI.LowerCallTo(CLI);
2103
2104 if (!CallInfo.second.getNode()) {
2105 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Created tailcall: "; DAG.getRoot().dump());
2106 // It's a tailcall, return the chain (which is the DAG root).
2107 return DAG.getRoot();
2108 }
2109
2110 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Created libcall: "; CallInfo.first.dump());
2111 return CallInfo.first;
2112}
