2114// Expand a node into a call to a libcall. Similar to
2115// ExpandLibCall except that the first operand is the in-chain.
2116std::pair<SDValue, SDValue>
2117SelectionDAGLegalize::ExpandChainLibCall(RTLIB::Libcall LC,
2118 SDNode *Node,
2119 bool isSigned) {
2120 SDValue InChain = Node->getOperand(0);
2121
2122 TargetLowering::ArgListTy Args;
2123 TargetLowering::ArgListEntry Entry;
2124 for (unsigned i = 1, e = Node->getNumOperands(); i != e; ++i) {
2125 EVT ArgVT = Node->getOperand(i).getValueType();
2126 Type *ArgTy = ArgVT.getTypeForEVT(*DAG.getContext());
2127 Entry.Node = Node->getOperand(i);
2128 Entry.Ty = ArgTy;
2129 Entry.IsSExt = isSigned;
2130 Entry.IsZExt = !isSigned;
2131 Args.push_back(Entry);
2132 }
2133 SDValue Callee = DAG.getExternalFunctionSymbol(TLI.getLibcallName(LC));
2134
2135 Type *RetTy = Node->getValueType(0).getTypeForEVT(*DAG.getContext());
2136
2137 TargetLowering::CallLoweringInfo CLI(DAG);
2138 CLI.setDebugLoc(SDLoc(Node))
2139 .setChain(InChain)
2140 .setLibCallee(TLI.getLibcallCallingConv(LC), RetTy, Callee,
2141 std::move(Args))
2142 .setSExtResult(isSigned)
2143 .setZExtResult(!isSigned);
2144
2145 std::pair<SDValue, SDValue> CallInfo = TLI.LowerCallTo(CLI);
2146
2147 return CallInfo;
2148}

2209
2210/// Issue libcalls to __{u}divmod to compute div / rem pairs.
2211void
2212SelectionDAGLegalize::ExpandDivRemLibCall(SDNode *Node,
2213 SmallVectorImpl<SDValue> &Results) {
2214 unsigned Opcode = Node->getOpcode();
2215 bool isSigned = Opcode == ISD::SDIVREM;
2216
2217 RTLIB::Libcall LC;
2218 switch (Node->getSimpleValueType(0).SimpleTy) {
2219 default: llvm_unreachable("Unexpected request for libcall!");
2220 case MVT::i8: LC= isSigned ? RTLIB::SDIVREM_I8 : RTLIB::UDIVREM_I8; break;
2221 case MVT::i16: LC= isSigned ? RTLIB::SDIVREM_I16 : RTLIB::UDIVREM_I16; break;
2222 case MVT::i32: LC= isSigned ? RTLIB::SDIVREM_I32 : RTLIB::UDIVREM_I32; break;
2223 case MVT::i64: LC= isSigned ? RTLIB::SDIVREM_I64 : RTLIB::UDIVREM_I64; break;
2224 case MVT::i128: LC= isSigned ? RTLIB::SDIVREM_I128:RTLIB::UDIVREM_I128; break;
2225 }
2226
2227 // The input chain to this libcall is the entry node of the function.
2228 // Legalizing the call will automatically add the previous call to the
2229 // dependence.
2230 SDValue InChain = DAG.getEntryNode();
2231
2232 EVT RetVT = Node->getValueType(0);
2233 Type *RetTy = RetVT.getTypeForEVT(*DAG.getContext());
2234
2235 TargetLowering::ArgListTy Args;
2236 TargetLowering::ArgListEntry Entry;
2237 for (const SDValue &Op : Node->op_values()) {
2238 EVT ArgVT = Op.getValueType();
2239 Type *ArgTy = ArgVT.getTypeForEVT(*DAG.getContext());
2240 Entry.Node = Op;
2241 Entry.Ty = ArgTy;
2242 Entry.IsSExt = isSigned;
2243 Entry.IsZExt = !isSigned;
2244 Args.push_back(Entry);
2245 }
2246
2247 // Also pass the return address of the remainder.
2248 SDValue FIPtr = DAG.CreateStackTemporary(RetVT);
2249 Entry.Node = FIPtr;
2250 Entry.Ty = RetTy->getPointerTo();
2251 Entry.IsSExt = isSigned;
2252 Entry.IsZExt = !isSigned;
2253 Args.push_back(Entry);
2254
2255 SDValue Callee = DAG.getExternalFunctionSymbol(TLI.getLibcallName(LC));
2256
2257 SDLoc dl(Node);
2258 TargetLowering::CallLoweringInfo CLI(DAG);
2259 CLI.setDebugLoc(dl)
2260 .setChain(InChain)
2261 .setLibCallee(TLI.getLibcallCallingConv(LC), RetTy, Callee,
2262 std::move(Args))
2263 .setSExtResult(isSigned)
2264 .setZExtResult(!isSigned);
2265
2266 std::pair<SDValue, SDValue> CallInfo = TLI.LowerCallTo(CLI);
2267
2268 // Remainder is loaded back from the stack frame.
2269 SDValue Rem =
2270 DAG.getLoad(RetVT, dl, CallInfo.second, FIPtr, MachinePointerInfo());
2271 Results.push_back(CallInfo.first);
2272 Results.push_back(Rem);
2273}

2275/// Return true if sincos libcall is available.
2276static bool isSinCosLibcallAvailable(SDNode *Node, const TargetLowering &TLI) {
2277 RTLIB::Libcall LC;
2278 switch (Node->getSimpleValueType(0).SimpleTy) {
2279 default: llvm_unreachable("Unexpected request for libcall!");
2280 case MVT::f32: LC = RTLIB::SINCOS_F32; break;
2281 case MVT::f64: LC = RTLIB::SINCOS_F64; break;
2282 case MVT::f80: LC = RTLIB::SINCOS_F80; break;
2283 case MVT::f128: LC = RTLIB::SINCOS_F128; break;
2284 case MVT::ppcf128: LC = RTLIB::SINCOS_PPCF128; break;
2285 }
2286 return TLI.getLibcallName(LC) != nullptr;
2287}
2288
2289/// Only issue sincos libcall if both sin and cos are needed.
2290static bool useSinCos(SDNode *Node) {
2291 unsigned OtherOpcode = Node->getOpcode() == ISD::FSIN
2292 ? ISD::FCOS : ISD::FSIN;
2293
2294 SDValue Op0 = Node->getOperand(0);
2295 for (SDNode::use_iterator UI = Op0.getNode()->use_begin(),
2296 UE = Op0.getNode()->use_end(); UI != UE; ++UI) {
2297 SDNode *User = *UI;
2298 if (User == Node)
2299 continue;
2300 // The other user might have been turned into sincos already.
2301 if (User->getOpcode() == OtherOpcode || User->getOpcode() == ISD::FSINCOS)
2302 return true;
2303 }
2304 return false;
2305}

2307/// Issue libcalls to sincos to compute sin / cos pairs.
2308void
2309SelectionDAGLegalize::ExpandSinCosLibCall(SDNode *Node,
2310 SmallVectorImpl<SDValue> &Results) {
2311 RTLIB::Libcall LC;
2312 switch (Node->getSimpleValueType(0).SimpleTy) {
2313 default: llvm_unreachable("Unexpected request for libcall!");
2314 case MVT::f32: LC = RTLIB::SINCOS_F32; break;
2315 case MVT::f64: LC = RTLIB::SINCOS_F64; break;
2316 case MVT::f80: LC = RTLIB::SINCOS_F80; break;
2317 case MVT::f128: LC = RTLIB::SINCOS_F128; break;
2318 case MVT::ppcf128: LC = RTLIB::SINCOS_PPCF128; break;
2319 }
2320
2321 // The input chain to this libcall is the entry node of the function.
2322 // Legalizing the call will automatically add the previous call to the
2323 // dependence.
2324 SDValue InChain = DAG.getEntryNode();
2325
2326 EVT RetVT = Node->getValueType(0);
2327 Type *RetTy = RetVT.getTypeForEVT(*DAG.getContext());
2328
2329 TargetLowering::ArgListTy Args;
2330 TargetLowering::ArgListEntry Entry;
2331
2332 // Pass the argument.
2333 Entry.Node = Node->getOperand(0);
2334 Entry.Ty = RetTy;
2335 Entry.IsSExt = false;
2336 Entry.IsZExt = false;
2337 Args.push_back(Entry);
2338
2339 // Pass the return address of sin.
2340 SDValue SinPtr = DAG.CreateStackTemporary(RetVT);
2341 Entry.Node = SinPtr;
2342 Entry.Ty = RetTy->getPointerTo();
2343 Entry.IsSExt = false;
2344 Entry.IsZExt = false;
2345 Args.push_back(Entry);
2346
2347 // Also pass the return address of the cos.
2348 SDValue CosPtr = DAG.CreateStackTemporary(RetVT);
2349 Entry.Node = CosPtr;
2350 Entry.Ty = RetTy->getPointerTo();
2351 Entry.IsSExt = false;
2352 Entry.IsZExt = false;
2353 Args.push_back(Entry);
2354
2355 SDValue Callee = DAG.getExternalFunctionSymbol(TLI.getLibcallName(LC));
2356
2357 SDLoc dl(Node);
2358 TargetLowering::CallLoweringInfo CLI(DAG);
2359 CLI.setDebugLoc(dl).setChain(InChain).setLibCallee(
2360 TLI.getLibcallCallingConv(LC), Type::getVoidTy(*DAG.getContext()), Callee,
2361 std::move(Args));
2362
2363 std::pair<SDValue, SDValue> CallInfo = TLI.LowerCallTo(CLI);
2364
2365 Results.push_back(
2366 DAG.getLoad(RetVT, dl, CallInfo.second, SinPtr, MachinePointerInfo()));
2367 Results.push_back(
2368 DAG.getLoad(RetVT, dl, CallInfo.second, CosPtr, MachinePointerInfo()));

2371/// This function is responsible for legalizing a
2372/// INT_TO_FP operation of the specified operand when the target requests that
2373/// we expand it. At this point, we know that the result and operand types are
2374/// legal for the target.
2375SDValue SelectionDAGLegalize::ExpandLegalINT_TO_FP(bool isSigned, SDValue Op0,
2376 EVT DestVT,
2377 const SDLoc &dl) {
2378 EVT SrcVT = Op0.getValueType();
2379
2380 // TODO: Should any fast-math-flags be set for the created nodes?
2381 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Legalizing INT_TO_FP\n");
2382 if (SrcVT == MVT::i32 && TLI.isTypeLegal(MVT::f64)) {
2383 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "32-bit [signed|unsigned] integer to float/double "
2384 "expansion\n");
2385
2386 // Get the stack frame index of a 8 byte buffer.
2387 SDValue StackSlot = DAG.CreateStackTemporary(MVT::f64);
2388
2389 // word offset constant for Hi/Lo address computation
2390 SDValue WordOff = DAG.getConstant(sizeof(int), dl,
2391 StackSlot.getValueType());
2392 // set up Hi and Lo (into buffer) address based on endian
2393 SDValue Hi = StackSlot;
2394 SDValue Lo = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, dl, StackSlot.getValueType(),
2395 StackSlot, WordOff);
2396 if (DAG.getDataLayout().isLittleEndian())
2397 std::swap(Hi, Lo);
2398
2399 // if signed map to unsigned space
2400 SDValue Op0Mapped;
2401 if (isSigned) {
2402 // constant used to invert sign bit (signed to unsigned mapping)
2403 SDValue SignBit = DAG.getConstant(0x80000000u, dl, MVT::i32);
2404 Op0Mapped = DAG.getNode(ISD::XOR, dl, MVT::i32, Op0, SignBit);
2405 } else {
2406 Op0Mapped = Op0;
2407 }
2408 // store the lo of the constructed double - based on integer input
2409 SDValue Store1 = DAG.getStore(DAG.getEntryNode(), dl, Op0Mapped, Lo,
2410 MachinePointerInfo());
2411 // initial hi portion of constructed double
2412 SDValue InitialHi = DAG.getConstant(0x43300000u, dl, MVT::i32);
2413 // store the hi of the constructed double - biased exponent
2414 SDValue Store2 =
2415 DAG.getStore(Store1, dl, InitialHi, Hi, MachinePointerInfo());
2416 // load the constructed double
2417 SDValue Load =
2418 DAG.getLoad(MVT::f64, dl, Store2, StackSlot, MachinePointerInfo());
2419 // FP constant to bias correct the final result
2420 SDValue Bias = DAG.getConstantFP(isSigned ?
2421 BitsToDouble(0x4330000080000000ULL) :
2422 BitsToDouble(0x4330000000000000ULL),
2423 dl, MVT::f64);
2424 // subtract the bias
2425 SDValue Sub = DAG.getNode(ISD::FSUB, dl, MVT::f64, Load, Bias);
2426 // final result
2427 SDValue Result = DAG.getFPExtendOrRound(Sub, dl, DestVT);
2428 return Result;
2429 }
2430 assert(!isSigned && "Legalize cannot Expand SINT_TO_FP for i64 yet");
2431 // Code below here assumes !isSigned without checking again.
2432
2433 SDValue Tmp1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::SINT_TO_FP, dl, DestVT, Op0);
2434
2435 SDValue SignSet = DAG.getSetCC(dl, getSetCCResultType(SrcVT), Op0,
2436 DAG.getConstant(0, dl, SrcVT), ISD::SETLT);
2437 SDValue Zero = DAG.getIntPtrConstant(0, dl),
2438 Four = DAG.getIntPtrConstant(4, dl);
2439 SDValue CstOffset = DAG.getSelect(dl, Zero.getValueType(),
2440 SignSet, Four, Zero);
2441
2442 // If the sign bit of the integer is set, the large number will be treated
2443 // as a negative number. To counteract this, the dynamic code adds an
2444 // offset depending on the data type.
2445 uint64_t FF;
2446 switch (SrcVT.getSimpleVT().SimpleTy) {
2447 default: llvm_unreachable("Unsupported integer type!");
2448 case MVT::i8 : FF = 0x43800000ULL; break; // 2^8 (as a float)
2449 case MVT::i16: FF = 0x47800000ULL; break; // 2^16 (as a float)
2450 case MVT::i32: FF = 0x4F800000ULL; break; // 2^32 (as a float)
2451 case MVT::i64: FF = 0x5F800000ULL; break; // 2^64 (as a float)
2452 }
2453 if (DAG.getDataLayout().isLittleEndian())
2454 FF <<= 32;
2455 Constant *FudgeFactor = ConstantInt::get(
2456 Type::getInt64Ty(*DAG.getContext()), FF);
2457
2458 SDValue CPIdx = DAG.getConstantPool(
2459 FudgeFactor,
2460 TLI.getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout(),
2461 DAG.getDataLayout().getGlobalsAddressSpace()));
2462 unsigned Alignment = cast<ConstantPoolSDNode>(CPIdx)->getAlignment();
2463 CPIdx = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, dl, CPIdx.getValueType(), CPIdx, CstOffset);
2464 Alignment = std::min(Alignment, 4u);
2465 SDValue FudgeInReg;
2466 if (DestVT == MVT::f32)
2467 FudgeInReg = DAG.getLoad(
2468 MVT::f32, dl, DAG.getEntryNode(), CPIdx,
2469 MachinePointerInfo::getConstantPool(DAG.getMachineFunction()),
2470 Alignment);
2471 else {
2472 SDValue Load = DAG.getExtLoad(
2473 ISD::EXTLOAD, dl, DestVT, DAG.getEntryNode(), CPIdx,
2474 MachinePointerInfo::getConstantPool(DAG.getMachineFunction()), MVT::f32,
2475 Alignment);
2476 HandleSDNode Handle(Load);
2477 LegalizeOp(Load.getNode());
2478 FudgeInReg = Handle.getValue();
2479 }
2480
2481 return DAG.getNode(ISD::FADD, dl, DestVT, Tmp1, FudgeInReg);
2482}

2484/// This function is responsible for legalizing a
2485/// *INT_TO_FP operation of the specified operand when the target requests that
2486/// we promote it. At this point, we know that the result and operand types are
2487/// legal for the target, and that there is a legal UINT_TO_FP or SINT_TO_FP
2488/// operation that takes a larger input.
2489SDValue SelectionDAGLegalize::PromoteLegalINT_TO_FP(SDValue LegalOp, EVT DestVT,
2490 bool isSigned,
2491 const SDLoc &dl) {
2492 // First step, figure out the appropriate *INT_TO_FP operation to use.
2493 EVT NewInTy = LegalOp.getValueType();
2494
2495 unsigned OpToUse = 0;
2496
2497 // Scan for the appropriate larger type to use.
2498 while (true) {
2499 NewInTy = (MVT::SimpleValueType)(NewInTy.getSimpleVT().SimpleTy+1);
2500 assert(NewInTy.isInteger() && "Ran out of possibilities!");
2501
2502 // If the target supports SINT_TO_FP of this type, use it.
2503 if (TLI.isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::SINT_TO_FP, NewInTy)) {
2504 OpToUse = ISD::SINT_TO_FP;
2505 break;
2506 }
2507 if (isSigned) continue;
2508
2509 // If the target supports UINT_TO_FP of this type, use it.
2510 if (TLI.isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::UINT_TO_FP, NewInTy)) {
2511 OpToUse = ISD::UINT_TO_FP;
2512 break;
2513 }
2514
2515 // Otherwise, try a larger type.
2516 }
2517
2518 // Okay, we found the operation and type to use. Zero extend our input to the
2519 // desired type then run the operation on it.
2520 return DAG.getNode(OpToUse, dl, DestVT,
2521 DAG.getNode(isSigned ? ISD::SIGN_EXTEND : ISD::ZERO_EXTEND,
2522 dl, NewInTy, LegalOp));
2523}
2524
2525/// This function is responsible for legalizing a
2526/// FP_TO_*INT operation of the specified operand when the target requests that
2527/// we promote it. At this point, we know that the result and operand types are
2528/// legal for the target, and that there is a legal FP_TO_UINT or FP_TO_SINT
2529/// operation that returns a larger result.
2530SDValue SelectionDAGLegalize::PromoteLegalFP_TO_INT(SDValue LegalOp, EVT DestVT,
2531 bool isSigned,
2532 const SDLoc &dl) {
2533 // First step, figure out the appropriate FP_TO*INT operation to use.
2534 EVT NewOutTy = DestVT;
2535
2536 unsigned OpToUse = 0;
2537
2538 // Scan for the appropriate larger type to use.
2539 while (true) {
2540 NewOutTy = (MVT::SimpleValueType)(NewOutTy.getSimpleVT().SimpleTy+1);
2541 assert(NewOutTy.isInteger() && "Ran out of possibilities!");
2542
2543 // A larger signed type can hold all unsigned values of the requested type,
2544 // so using FP_TO_SINT is valid
2545 if (TLI.isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::FP_TO_SINT, NewOutTy)) {
2546 OpToUse = ISD::FP_TO_SINT;
2547 break;
2548 }
2549
2550 // However, if the value may be < 0.0, we *must* use some FP_TO_SINT.
2551 if (!isSigned && TLI.isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::FP_TO_UINT, NewOutTy)) {
2552 OpToUse = ISD::FP_TO_UINT;
2553 break;
2554 }
2555
2556 // Otherwise, try a larger type.
2557 }
2558
2559 // Okay, we found the operation and type to use.
2560 SDValue Operation = DAG.getNode(OpToUse, dl, NewOutTy, LegalOp);
2561
2562 // Truncate the result of the extended FP_TO_*INT operation to the desired
2563 // size.
2564 return DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, dl, DestVT, Operation);
2565}

2567/// Legalize a BITREVERSE scalar/vector operation as a series of mask + shifts.
2568SDValue SelectionDAGLegalize::ExpandBITREVERSE(SDValue Op, const SDLoc &dl) {
2569 EVT VT = Op.getValueType();
2570 EVT SHVT = TLI.getShiftAmountTy(VT, DAG.getDataLayout());
2571 unsigned Sz = VT.getScalarSizeInBits();
2572
2573 SDValue Tmp, Tmp2, Tmp3;
2574
2575 // If we can, perform BSWAP first and then the mask+swap the i4, then i2
2576 // and finally the i1 pairs.
2577 // TODO: We can easily support i4/i2 legal types if any target ever does.
2578 if (Sz >= 8 && isPowerOf2_32(Sz)) {
2579 // Create the masks - repeating the pattern every byte.
2580 APInt MaskHi4 = APInt::getSplat(Sz, APInt(8, 0xF0));
2581 APInt MaskHi2 = APInt::getSplat(Sz, APInt(8, 0xCC));
2582 APInt MaskHi1 = APInt::getSplat(Sz, APInt(8, 0xAA));
2583 APInt MaskLo4 = APInt::getSplat(Sz, APInt(8, 0x0F));
2584 APInt MaskLo2 = APInt::getSplat(Sz, APInt(8, 0x33));
2585 APInt MaskLo1 = APInt::getSplat(Sz, APInt(8, 0x55));
2586
2587 // BSWAP if the type is wider than a single byte.
2588 Tmp = (Sz > 8 ? DAG.getNode(ISD::BSWAP, dl, VT, Op) : Op);
2589
2590 // swap i4: ((V & 0xF0) >> 4) | ((V & 0x0F) << 4)
2591 Tmp2 = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, VT, Tmp, DAG.getConstant(MaskHi4, dl, VT));
2592 Tmp3 = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, VT, Tmp, DAG.getConstant(MaskLo4, dl, VT));
2593 Tmp2 = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, dl, VT, Tmp2, DAG.getConstant(4, dl, SHVT));
2594 Tmp3 = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, dl, VT, Tmp3, DAG.getConstant(4, dl, SHVT));
2595 Tmp = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, dl, VT, Tmp2, Tmp3);
2596
2597 // swap i2: ((V & 0xCC) >> 2) | ((V & 0x33) << 2)
2598 Tmp2 = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, VT, Tmp, DAG.getConstant(MaskHi2, dl, VT));
2599 Tmp3 = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, VT, Tmp, DAG.getConstant(MaskLo2, dl, VT));
2600 Tmp2 = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, dl, VT, Tmp2, DAG.getConstant(2, dl, SHVT));
2601 Tmp3 = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, dl, VT, Tmp3, DAG.getConstant(2, dl, SHVT));
2602 Tmp = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, dl, VT, Tmp2, Tmp3);
2603
2604 // swap i1: ((V & 0xAA) >> 1) | ((V & 0x55) << 1)
2605 Tmp2 = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, VT, Tmp, DAG.getConstant(MaskHi1, dl, VT));
2606 Tmp3 = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, VT, Tmp, DAG.getConstant(MaskLo1, dl, VT));
2607 Tmp2 = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, dl, VT, Tmp2, DAG.getConstant(1, dl, SHVT));
2608 Tmp3 = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, dl, VT, Tmp3, DAG.getConstant(1, dl, SHVT));
2609 Tmp = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, dl, VT, Tmp2, Tmp3);
2610 return Tmp;
2611 }
2612
2613 Tmp = DAG.getConstant(0, dl, VT);
2614 for (unsigned I = 0, J = Sz-1; I < Sz; ++I, --J) {
2615 if (I < J)
2616 Tmp2 =
2617 DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, dl, VT, Op, DAG.getConstant(J - I, dl, SHVT));
2618 else
2619 Tmp2 =
2620 DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, dl, VT, Op, DAG.getConstant(I - J, dl, SHVT));
2621
2622 APInt Shift(Sz, 1);
2623 Shift <<= J;
2624 Tmp2 = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, VT, Tmp2, DAG.getConstant(Shift, dl, VT));
2625 Tmp = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, dl, VT, Tmp, Tmp2);
2626 }
2627
2628 return Tmp;
2629}

2631/// Open code the operations for BSWAP of the specified operation.
2632SDValue SelectionDAGLegalize::ExpandBSWAP(SDValue Op, const SDLoc &dl) {
2633 EVT VT = Op.getValueType();
2634 EVT SHVT = TLI.getShiftAmountTy(VT, DAG.getDataLayout());
2635 SDValue Tmp1, Tmp2, Tmp3, Tmp4, Tmp5, Tmp6, Tmp7, Tmp8;
2636 switch (VT.getSimpleVT().getScalarType().SimpleTy) {
2637 default: llvm_unreachable("Unhandled Expand type in BSWAP!");
2638 case MVT::i16:
2639 // Use a rotate by 8. This can be further expanded if necessary.
2640 return DAG.getNode(ISD::ROTL, dl, VT, Op, DAG.getConstant(8, dl, SHVT));
2641 case MVT::i32:
2642 Tmp4 = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, dl, VT, Op, DAG.getConstant(24, dl, SHVT));
2643 Tmp3 = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, dl, VT, Op, DAG.getConstant(8, dl, SHVT));
2644 Tmp2 = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, dl, VT, Op, DAG.getConstant(8, dl, SHVT));
2645 Tmp1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, dl, VT, Op, DAG.getConstant(24, dl, SHVT));
2646 Tmp3 = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, VT, Tmp3,
2647 DAG.getConstant(0xFF0000, dl, VT));
2648 Tmp2 = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, VT, Tmp2, DAG.getConstant(0xFF00, dl, VT));
2649 Tmp4 = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, dl, VT, Tmp4, Tmp3);
2650 Tmp2 = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, dl, VT, Tmp2, Tmp1);
2651 return DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, dl, VT, Tmp4, Tmp2);
2652 case MVT::i64:
2653 Tmp8 = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, dl, VT, Op, DAG.getConstant(56, dl, SHVT));
2654 Tmp7 = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, dl, VT, Op, DAG.getConstant(40, dl, SHVT));
2655 Tmp6 = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, dl, VT, Op, DAG.getConstant(24, dl, SHVT));
2656 Tmp5 = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, dl, VT, Op, DAG.getConstant(8, dl, SHVT));
2657 Tmp4 = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, dl, VT, Op, DAG.getConstant(8, dl, SHVT));
2658 Tmp3 = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, dl, VT, Op, DAG.getConstant(24, dl, SHVT));
2659 Tmp2 = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, dl, VT, Op, DAG.getConstant(40, dl, SHVT));
2660 Tmp1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, dl, VT, Op, DAG.getConstant(56, dl, SHVT));
2661 Tmp7 = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, VT, Tmp7,
2662 DAG.getConstant(255ULL<<48, dl, VT));
2663 Tmp6 = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, VT, Tmp6,
2664 DAG.getConstant(255ULL<<40, dl, VT));
2665 Tmp5 = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, VT, Tmp5,
2666 DAG.getConstant(255ULL<<32, dl, VT));
2667 Tmp4 = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, VT, Tmp4,
2668 DAG.getConstant(255ULL<<24, dl, VT));
2669 Tmp3 = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, VT, Tmp3,
2670 DAG.getConstant(255ULL<<16, dl, VT));
2671 Tmp2 = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, VT, Tmp2,
2672 DAG.getConstant(255ULL<<8 , dl, VT));
2673 Tmp8 = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, dl, VT, Tmp8, Tmp7);
2674 Tmp6 = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, dl, VT, Tmp6, Tmp5);
2675 Tmp4 = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, dl, VT, Tmp4, Tmp3);
2676 Tmp2 = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, dl, VT, Tmp2, Tmp1);
2677 Tmp8 = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, dl, VT, Tmp8, Tmp6);
2678 Tmp4 = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, dl, VT, Tmp4, Tmp2);
2679 return DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, dl, VT, Tmp8, Tmp4);
2680 }

2682
2683bool SelectionDAGLegalize::ExpandNode(SDNode *Node) {
2684 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Trying to expand node\n");
2685 SmallVector<SDValue, 8> Results;
2686 SDLoc dl(Node);
2687 SDValue Tmp1, Tmp2, Tmp3, Tmp4;
2688 bool NeedInvert;
2689 switch (Node->getOpcode()) {
2690 case ISD::ABS:
2691 if (TLI.expandABS(Node, Tmp1, DAG))
2692 Results.push_back(Tmp1);
2693 break;
2694 case ISD::CTPOP:
2695 if (TLI.expandCTPOP(Node, Tmp1, DAG))
2696 Results.push_back(Tmp1);
2697 break;
2698 case ISD::CTLZ:
2699 case ISD::CTLZ_ZERO_UNDEF:
2700 if (TLI.expandCTLZ(Node, Tmp1, DAG))
2701 Results.push_back(Tmp1);
2702 break;
2703 case ISD::CTTZ:
2704 case ISD::CTTZ_ZERO_UNDEF:
2705 if (TLI.expandCTTZ(Node, Tmp1, DAG))
2706 Results.push_back(Tmp1);
2707 break;
2708 case ISD::BITREVERSE:
2709 Results.push_back(ExpandBITREVERSE(Node->getOperand(0), dl));
2710 break;
2711 case ISD::BSWAP:
2712 Results.push_back(ExpandBSWAP(Node->getOperand(0), dl));
2713 break;
2714 case ISD::FRAMEADDR:
2715 case ISD::RETURNADDR:
2716 case ISD::FRAME_TO_ARGS_OFFSET:
2717 Results.push_back(DAG.getConstant(0, dl, Node->getValueType(0)));
2718 break;
2719 case ISD::EH_DWARF_CFA: {
2720 unsigned DwarfAS = 0; // FIXME: is this correct?
2721 SDValue CfaArg =
2722 DAG.getSExtOrTrunc(Node->getOperand(0), dl,
2723 TLI.getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout(), DwarfAS));
2724 SDValue Offset = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, dl,
2725 CfaArg.getValueType(),
2726 DAG.getNode(ISD::FRAME_TO_ARGS_OFFSET, dl,
2727 CfaArg.getValueType()),
2728 CfaArg);
2729 SDValue FA = DAG.getNode(
2730 ISD::FRAMEADDR, dl, TLI.getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout(), DwarfAS),
2731 DAG.getConstant(0, dl, TLI.getPointerRangeTy(DAG.getDataLayout())));
2732 Results.push_back(DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, dl, FA.getValueType(),
2733 FA, Offset));

2735 }
2736 case ISD::FLT_ROUNDS_:
2737 Results.push_back(DAG.getConstant(1, dl, Node->getValueType(0)));
2738 break;
2739 case ISD::EH_RETURN:
2740 case ISD::EH_LABEL:
2741 case ISD::PREFETCH:
2742 case ISD::VAEND:
2743 case ISD::EH_SJLJ_LONGJMP:
2744 // If the target didn't expand these, there's nothing to do, so just
2745 // preserve the chain and be done.
2746 Results.push_back(Node->getOperand(0));
2747 break;
2748 case ISD::READCYCLECOUNTER:
2749 // If the target didn't expand this, just return 'zero' and preserve the
2750 // chain.
2751 Results.append(Node->getNumValues() - 1,
2752 DAG.getConstant(0, dl, Node->getValueType(0)));
2753 Results.push_back(Node->getOperand(0));
2754 break;
2755 case ISD::EH_SJLJ_SETJMP:
2756 // If the target didn't expand this, just return 'zero' and preserve the
2757 // chain.
2758 Results.push_back(DAG.getConstant(0, dl, MVT::i32));
2759 Results.push_back(Node->getOperand(0));
2760 break;
2761 case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD: {
2762 // There is no libcall for atomic load; fake it with ATOMIC_CMP_SWAP.
2763 SDValue Zero = DAG.getConstant(0, dl, Node->getValueType(0));
2764 SDVTList VTs = DAG.getVTList(Node->getValueType(0), MVT::Other);
2765 SDValue Swap = DAG.getAtomicCmpSwap(
2766 ISD::ATOMIC_CMP_SWAP, dl, cast<AtomicSDNode>(Node)->getMemoryVT(), VTs,
2767 Node->getOperand(0), Node->getOperand(1), Zero, Zero,
2768 cast<AtomicSDNode>(Node)->getMemOperand());
2769 Results.push_back(Swap.getValue(0));
2770 Results.push_back(Swap.getValue(1));
2771 break;
2772 }
2773 case ISD::ATOMIC_STORE: {
2774 // There is no libcall for atomic store; fake it with ATOMIC_SWAP.
2775 SDValue Swap = DAG.getAtomic(ISD::ATOMIC_SWAP, dl,
2776 cast<AtomicSDNode>(Node)->getMemoryVT(),
2777 Node->getOperand(0),
2778 Node->getOperand(1), Node->getOperand(2),
2779 cast<AtomicSDNode>(Node)->getMemOperand());
2780 Results.push_back(Swap.getValue(1));
2781 break;
2782 }
2783 case ISD::ATOMIC_CMP_SWAP_WITH_SUCCESS: {
2784 // Expanding an ATOMIC_CMP_SWAP_WITH_SUCCESS produces an ATOMIC_CMP_SWAP and
2785 // splits out the success value as a comparison. Expanding the resulting
2786 // ATOMIC_CMP_SWAP will produce a libcall.
2787 SDVTList VTs = DAG.getVTList(Node->getValueType(0), MVT::Other);
2788 SDValue Res = DAG.getAtomicCmpSwap(
2789 ISD::ATOMIC_CMP_SWAP, dl, cast<AtomicSDNode>(Node)->getMemoryVT(), VTs,
2790 Node->getOperand(0), Node->getOperand(1), Node->getOperand(2),
2791 Node->getOperand(3), cast<MemSDNode>(Node)->getMemOperand());
2792
2793 SDValue ExtRes = Res;
2794 SDValue LHS = Res;
2795 SDValue RHS = Node->getOperand(2);
2796
2797 EVT AtomicType = cast<AtomicSDNode>(Node)->getMemoryVT();
2798 EVT OuterType = Node->getValueType(0);
2799 // XXXAR: Sign/Zero extending fat pointers doesn't make sense -> skip this
2800 if (!OuterType.isFatPointer()) {
2801 // XXXAR: not indented correctly to avoid merge conflicts
2802 switch (TLI.getExtendForAtomicOps()) {
2803 case ISD::SIGN_EXTEND:
2804 LHS = DAG.getNode(ISD::AssertSext, dl, OuterType, Res,
2805 DAG.getValueType(AtomicType));
2806 RHS = DAG.getNode(ISD::SIGN_EXTEND_INREG, dl, OuterType,
2807 Node->getOperand(2), DAG.getValueType(AtomicType));
2808 ExtRes = LHS;
2809 break;
2810 case ISD::ZERO_EXTEND:
2811 LHS = DAG.getNode(ISD::AssertZext, dl, OuterType, Res,
2812 DAG.getValueType(AtomicType));
2813 RHS = DAG.getZeroExtendInReg(Node->getOperand(2), dl, AtomicType);
2814 ExtRes = LHS;
2815 break;
2816 case ISD::ANY_EXTEND:
2817 LHS = DAG.getZeroExtendInReg(Res, dl, AtomicType);
2818 RHS = DAG.getZeroExtendInReg(Node->getOperand(2), dl, AtomicType);
2819 break;
2820 default:
2821 llvm_unreachable("Invalid atomic op extension");
2822 }
2823 }
2824
2825 SDValue Success =
2826 DAG.getSetCC(dl, Node->getValueType(1), LHS, RHS, ISD::SETEQ);
2827
2828 Results.push_back(ExtRes.getValue(0));
2829 Results.push_back(Success);
2830 Results.push_back(Res.getValue(1));
2831 break;
2832 }
2833 case ISD::DYNAMIC_STACKALLOC:
2834 ExpandDYNAMIC_STACKALLOC(Node, Results);
2835 break;
2836 case ISD::MERGE_VALUES:
2837 for (unsigned i = 0; i < Node->getNumValues(); i++)
2838 Results.push_back(Node->getOperand(i));
2839 break;
2840 case ISD::UNDEF: {

2842 if (VT.isInteger())
2843 Results.push_back(DAG.getConstant(0, dl, VT));
2844 else {
2845 assert(VT.isFloatingPoint() && "Unknown value type!");
2846 Results.push_back(DAG.getConstantFP(0, dl, VT));
2847 }
2848 break;
2849 }
2850 case ISD::STRICT_FP_ROUND:
2851 Tmp1 = EmitStackConvert(Node->getOperand(1),
2852 Node->getValueType(0),
2853 Node->getValueType(0), dl, Node->getOperand(0));
2854 ReplaceNode(Node, Tmp1.getNode());
2855 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Successfully expanded STRICT_FP_ROUND node\n");
2856 return true;
2857 case ISD::FP_ROUND:

2860 Node->getValueType(0),
2861 Node->getValueType(0), dl);

2863 break;
2864 case ISD::STRICT_FP_EXTEND:

2871 case ISD::FP_EXTEND:
2872 Tmp1 = EmitStackConvert(Node->getOperand(0),
2873 Node->getOperand(0).getValueType(),
2874 Node->getValueType(0), dl);
2875 Results.push_back(Tmp1);
2876 break;
2877 case ISD::SIGN_EXTEND_INREG: {
2878 EVT ExtraVT = cast<VTSDNode>(Node->getOperand(1))->getVT();
2879 EVT VT = Node->getValueType(0);
2880
2881 // An in-register sign-extend of a boolean is a negation:
2882 // 'true' (1) sign-extended is -1.
2883 // 'false' (0) sign-extended is 0.
2884 // However, we must mask the high bits of the source operand because the
2885 // SIGN_EXTEND_INREG does not guarantee that the high bits are already zero.
2886

2888 if (ExtraVT.getSizeInBits() == 1) {
2889 SDValue One = DAG.getConstant(1, dl, VT);
2890 SDValue And = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, VT, Node->getOperand(0), One);
2891 SDValue Zero = DAG.getConstant(0, dl, VT);
2892 SDValue Neg = DAG.getNode(ISD::SUB, dl, VT, Zero, And);
2893 Results.push_back(Neg);
2894 break;

2898 // SRA. However, it is doubtful that any exist.

2900 unsigned BitsDiff = VT.getScalarSizeInBits() -
2901 ExtraVT.getScalarSizeInBits();
2902 SDValue ShiftCst = DAG.getConstant(BitsDiff, dl, ShiftAmountTy);
2903 Tmp1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, dl, Node->getValueType(0),
2904 Node->getOperand(0), ShiftCst);
2905 Tmp1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRA, dl, Node->getValueType(0), Tmp1, ShiftCst);
2906 Results.push_back(Tmp1);
2907 break;
2908 }
2909 case ISD::FP_ROUND_INREG: {

2914 // slots and always reusing the same one. We currently always create

2918 Node->getValueType(0), dl);
2919 Results.push_back(Tmp1);
2920 break;
2921 }

2951 RTLIB::LLROUND_PPCF128));

2969 case ISD::VACOPY:

2972 case ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT:

2990 case ISD::SCALAR_TO_VECTOR:

2993 case ISD::INSERT_VECTOR_ELT:

2998 case ISD::VECTOR_SHUFFLE: {
2999 SmallVector<int, 32> NewMask;
3000 ArrayRef<int> Mask = cast<ShuffleVectorSDNode>(Node)->getMask();
3001
3002 EVT VT = Node->getValueType(0);
3003 EVT EltVT = VT.getVectorElementType();
3004 SDValue Op0 = Node->getOperand(0);
3005 SDValue Op1 = Node->getOperand(1);
3006 if (!TLI.isTypeLegal(EltVT)) {
3007 EVT NewEltVT = TLI.getTypeToTransformTo(*DAG.getContext(), EltVT);
3008
3009 // BUILD_VECTOR operands are allowed to be wider than the element type.
3010 // But if NewEltVT is smaller that EltVT the BUILD_VECTOR does not accept
3011 // it.
3012 if (NewEltVT.bitsLT(EltVT)) {
3013 // Convert shuffle node.
3014 // If original node was v4i64 and the new EltVT is i32,
3015 // cast operands to v8i32 and re-build the mask.
3016
3017 // Calculate new VT, the size of the new VT should be equal to original.
3018 EVT NewVT =
3019 EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(), NewEltVT,
3020 VT.getSizeInBits() / NewEltVT.getSizeInBits());
3021 assert(NewVT.bitsEq(VT));
3022
3023 // cast operands to new VT
3024 Op0 = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, dl, NewVT, Op0);
3025 Op1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, dl, NewVT, Op1);
3026
3027 // Convert the shuffle mask
3028 unsigned int factor =
3029 NewVT.getVectorNumElements()/VT.getVectorNumElements();
3030
3031 // EltVT gets smaller
3032 assert(factor > 0);
3033
3034 for (unsigned i = 0; i < VT.getVectorNumElements(); ++i) {
3035 if (Mask[i] < 0) {
3036 for (unsigned fi = 0; fi < factor; ++fi)
3037 NewMask.push_back(Mask[i]);
3038 }
3039 else {
3040 for (unsigned fi = 0; fi < factor; ++fi)
3041 NewMask.push_back(Mask[i]*factor+fi);
3042 }
3043 }
3044 Mask = NewMask;
3045 VT = NewVT;
3046 }
3047 EltVT = NewEltVT;
3048 }
3049 unsigned NumElems = VT.getVectorNumElements();
3050 SmallVector<SDValue, 16> Ops;
3051 for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumElems; ++i) {
3052 if (Mask[i] < 0) {
3053 Ops.push_back(DAG.getUNDEF(EltVT));
3054 continue;
3055 }
3056 unsigned Idx = Mask[i];
3057 if (Idx < NumElems)
3058 Ops.push_back(DAG.getNode(
3059 ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, dl, EltVT, Op0,
3060 DAG.getConstant(Idx, dl, TLI.getVectorIdxTy(DAG.getDataLayout()))));
3061 else
3062 Ops.push_back(DAG.getNode(
3063 ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, dl, EltVT, Op1,
3064 DAG.getConstant(Idx - NumElems, dl,
3065 TLI.getVectorIdxTy(DAG.getDataLayout()))));
3066 }
3067
3068 Tmp1 = DAG.getBuildVector(VT, dl, Ops);
3069 // We may have changed the BUILD_VECTOR type. Cast it back to the Node type.
3070 Tmp1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, dl, Node->getValueType(0), Tmp1);
3071 Results.push_back(Tmp1);
3072 break;
3073 }
3074 case ISD::EXTRACT_ELEMENT: {
3075 EVT OpTy = Node->getOperand(0).getValueType();
3076 if (cast<ConstantSDNode>(Node->getOperand(1))->getZExtValue()) {
3077 // 1 -> Hi
3078 Tmp1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, dl, OpTy, Node->getOperand(0),
3079 DAG.getConstant(OpTy.getSizeInBits() / 2, dl,
3080 TLI.getShiftAmountTy(
3081 Node->getOperand(0).getValueType(),
3082 DAG.getDataLayout())));
3083 Tmp1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, dl, Node->getValueType(0), Tmp1);
3084 } else {
3085 // 0 -> Lo
3086 Tmp1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, dl, Node->getValueType(0),
3087 Node->getOperand(0));

3089 Results.push_back(Tmp1);

3118 case ISD::FCOPYSIGN:

3134 case ISD::UMIN:

3139 default: llvm_unreachable("How did we get here?");
3140 case ISD::SMAX: Pred = ISD::SETGT; break;
3141 case ISD::SMIN: Pred = ISD::SETLT; break;

3158 case ISD::FCOS: {

3200 }

3228 case ISD::SUB: {
3229 EVT VT = Node->getValueType(0);
3230 assert(TLI.isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::ADD, VT) &&
3231 TLI.isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::XOR, VT) &&
3232 "Don't know how to expand this subtraction!");
3233 Tmp1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::XOR, dl, VT, Node->getOperand(1),
3234 DAG.getConstant(APInt::getAllOnesValue(VT.getSizeInBits()), dl,
3235 VT));
3236 Tmp1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, dl, VT, Tmp1, DAG.getConstant(1, dl, VT));
3237 Results.push_back(DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, dl, VT, Node->getOperand(0), Tmp1));
3238 break;
3239 }
3240 case ISD::UREM:
3241 case ISD::SREM: {
3242 EVT VT = Node->getValueType(0);
3243 bool isSigned = Node->getOpcode() == ISD::SREM;
3244 unsigned DivOpc = isSigned ? ISD::SDIV : ISD::UDIV;
3245 unsigned DivRemOpc = isSigned ? ISD::SDIVREM : ISD::UDIVREM;
3246 Tmp2 = Node->getOperand(0);
3247 Tmp3 = Node->getOperand(1);
3248 if (TLI.isOperationLegalOrCustom(DivRemOpc, VT)) {
3249 SDVTList VTs = DAG.getVTList(VT, VT);
3250 Tmp1 = DAG.getNode(DivRemOpc, dl, VTs, Tmp2, Tmp3).getValue(1);
3251 Results.push_back(Tmp1);
3252 } else if (TLI.isOperationLegalOrCustom(DivOpc, VT)) {
3253 // X % Y -> X-X/Y*Y
3254 Tmp1 = DAG.getNode(DivOpc, dl, VT, Tmp2, Tmp3);
3255 Tmp1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::MUL, dl, VT, Tmp1, Tmp3);
3256 Tmp1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::SUB, dl, VT, Tmp2, Tmp1);
3257 Results.push_back(Tmp1);
3258 }
3259 break;
3260 }
3261 case ISD::UDIV:
3262 case ISD::SDIV: {
3263 bool isSigned = Node->getOpcode() == ISD::SDIV;
3264 unsigned DivRemOpc = isSigned ? ISD::SDIVREM : ISD::UDIVREM;
3265 EVT VT = Node->getValueType(0);
3266 if (TLI.isOperationLegalOrCustom(DivRemOpc, VT)) {
3267 SDVTList VTs = DAG.getVTList(VT, VT);
3268 Tmp1 = DAG.getNode(DivRemOpc, dl, VTs, Node->getOperand(0),
3269 Node->getOperand(1));
3270 Results.push_back(Tmp1);
3271 }
3272 break;
3273 }
3274 case ISD::MULHU:
3275 case ISD::MULHS: {
3276 unsigned ExpandOpcode =
3277 Node->getOpcode() == ISD::MULHU ? ISD::UMUL_LOHI : ISD::SMUL_LOHI;
3278 EVT VT = Node->getValueType(0);
3279 SDVTList VTs = DAG.getVTList(VT, VT);
3280
3281 Tmp1 = DAG.getNode(ExpandOpcode, dl, VTs, Node->getOperand(0),
3282 Node->getOperand(1));
3283 Results.push_back(Tmp1.getValue(1));
3284 break;
3285 }
3286 case ISD::UMUL_LOHI:
3287 case ISD::SMUL_LOHI: {
3288 SDValue LHS = Node->getOperand(0);
3289 SDValue RHS = Node->getOperand(1);
3290 MVT VT = LHS.getSimpleValueType();
3291 unsigned MULHOpcode =
3292 Node->getOpcode() == ISD::UMUL_LOHI ? ISD::MULHU : ISD::MULHS;
3293
3294 if (TLI.isOperationLegalOrCustom(MULHOpcode, VT)) {
3295 Results.push_back(DAG.getNode(ISD::MUL, dl, VT, LHS, RHS));
3296 Results.push_back(DAG.getNode(MULHOpcode, dl, VT, LHS, RHS));
3297 break;
3298 }
3299
3300 SmallVector<SDValue, 4> Halves;
3301 EVT HalfType = EVT(VT).getHalfSizedIntegerVT(*DAG.getContext());
3302 assert(TLI.isTypeLegal(HalfType));
3303 if (TLI.expandMUL_LOHI(Node->getOpcode(), VT, Node, LHS, RHS, Halves,
3304 HalfType, DAG,
3305 TargetLowering::MulExpansionKind::Always)) {
3306 for (unsigned i = 0; i < 2; ++i) {
3307 SDValue Lo = DAG.getNode(ISD::ZERO_EXTEND, dl, VT, Halves[2 * i]);
3308 SDValue Hi = DAG.getNode(ISD::ANY_EXTEND, dl, VT, Halves[2 * i + 1]);
3309 SDValue Shift = DAG.getConstant(
3310 HalfType.getScalarSizeInBits(), dl,
3311 TLI.getShiftAmountTy(HalfType, DAG.getDataLayout()));
3312 Hi = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, dl, VT, Hi, Shift);
3313 Results.push_back(DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, dl, VT, Lo, Hi));
3314 }
3315 break;
3316 }
3317 break;
3318 }
3319 case ISD::MUL: {
3320 EVT VT = Node->getValueType(0);
3321 SDVTList VTs = DAG.getVTList(VT, VT);
3322 // See if multiply or divide can be lowered using two-result operations.
3323 // We just need the low half of the multiply; try both the signed
3324 // and unsigned forms. If the target supports both SMUL_LOHI and
3325 // UMUL_LOHI, form a preference by checking which forms of plain
3326 // MULH it supports.
3327 bool HasSMUL_LOHI = TLI.isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::SMUL_LOHI, VT);
3328 bool HasUMUL_LOHI = TLI.isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::UMUL_LOHI, VT);
3329 bool HasMULHS = TLI.isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::MULHS, VT);
3330 bool HasMULHU = TLI.isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::MULHU, VT);
3331 unsigned OpToUse = 0;
3332 if (HasSMUL_LOHI && !HasMULHS) {
3333 OpToUse = ISD::SMUL_LOHI;
3334 } else if (HasUMUL_LOHI && !HasMULHU) {
3335 OpToUse = ISD::UMUL_LOHI;
3336 } else if (HasSMUL_LOHI) {
3337 OpToUse = ISD::SMUL_LOHI;
3338 } else if (HasUMUL_LOHI) {
3339 OpToUse = ISD::UMUL_LOHI;
3340 }
3341 if (OpToUse) {
3342 Results.push_back(DAG.getNode(OpToUse, dl, VTs, Node->getOperand(0),
3343 Node->getOperand(1)));
3344 break;
3345 }
3346
3347 SDValue Lo, Hi;
3348 EVT HalfType = VT.getHalfSizedIntegerVT(*DAG.getContext());
3349 if (TLI.isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::ZERO_EXTEND, VT) &&
3350 TLI.isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::ANY_EXTEND, VT) &&
3351 TLI.isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::SHL, VT) &&
3352 TLI.isOperationLegalOrCustom(ISD::OR, VT) &&
3353 TLI.expandMUL(Node, Lo, Hi, HalfType, DAG,
3354 TargetLowering::MulExpansionKind::OnlyLegalOrCustom)) {
3355 Lo = DAG.getNode(ISD::ZERO_EXTEND, dl, VT, Lo);
3356 Hi = DAG.getNode(ISD::ANY_EXTEND, dl, VT, Hi);
3357 SDValue Shift =
3358 DAG.getConstant(HalfType.getSizeInBits(), dl,
3359 TLI.getShiftAmountTy(HalfType, DAG.getDataLayout()));
3360 Hi = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, dl, VT, Hi, Shift);
3361 Results.push_back(DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, dl, VT, Lo, Hi));
3362 }
3363 break;
3364 }
3365 case ISD::FSHL:
3366 case ISD::FSHR:
3367 if (TLI.expandFunnelShift(Node, Tmp1, DAG))
3368 Results.push_back(Tmp1);
3369 break;
3370 case ISD::ROTL:
3371 case ISD::ROTR:
3372 if (TLI.expandROT(Node, Tmp1, DAG))
3373 Results.push_back(Tmp1);
3374 break;
3375 case ISD::SADDSAT:
3376 case ISD::UADDSAT:
3377 case ISD::SSUBSAT:
3378 case ISD::USUBSAT:
3379 Results.push_back(TLI.expandAddSubSat(Node, DAG));
3380 break;
3381 case ISD::SMULFIX:
3382 case ISD::SMULFIXSAT:
3383 case ISD::UMULFIX:
3384 Results.push_back(TLI.expandFixedPointMul(Node, DAG));
3385 break;
3386 case ISD::ADDCARRY:
3387 case ISD::SUBCARRY: {
3388 SDValue LHS = Node->getOperand(0);
3389 SDValue RHS = Node->getOperand(1);
3390 SDValue Carry = Node->getOperand(2);
3391
3392 bool IsAdd = Node->getOpcode() == ISD::ADDCARRY;
3393
3394 // Initial add of the 2 operands.
3395 unsigned Op = IsAdd ? ISD::ADD : ISD::SUB;
3396 EVT VT = LHS.getValueType();
3397 SDValue Sum = DAG.getNode(Op, dl, VT, LHS, RHS);
3398
3399 // Initial check for overflow.
3400 EVT CarryType = Node->getValueType(1);
3401 EVT SetCCType = getSetCCResultType(Node->getValueType(0));
3402 ISD::CondCode CC = IsAdd ? ISD::SETULT : ISD::SETUGT;
3403 SDValue Overflow = DAG.getSetCC(dl, SetCCType, Sum, LHS, CC);
3404
3405 // Add of the sum and the carry.
3406 SDValue CarryExt =
3407 DAG.getZeroExtendInReg(DAG.getZExtOrTrunc(Carry, dl, VT), dl, MVT::i1);
3408 SDValue Sum2 = DAG.getNode(Op, dl, VT, Sum, CarryExt);
3409
3410 // Second check for overflow. If we are adding, we can only overflow if the
3411 // initial sum is all 1s ang the carry is set, resulting in a new sum of 0.
3412 // If we are subtracting, we can only overflow if the initial sum is 0 and
3413 // the carry is set, resulting in a new sum of all 1s.
3414 SDValue Zero = DAG.getConstant(0, dl, VT);
3415 SDValue Overflow2 =
3416 IsAdd ? DAG.getSetCC(dl, SetCCType, Sum2, Zero, ISD::SETEQ)
3417 : DAG.getSetCC(dl, SetCCType, Sum, Zero, ISD::SETEQ);
3418 Overflow2 = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, SetCCType, Overflow2,
3419 DAG.getZExtOrTrunc(Carry, dl, SetCCType));
3420
3421 SDValue ResultCarry =
3422 DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, dl, SetCCType, Overflow, Overflow2);
3423
3424 Results.push_back(Sum2);
3425 Results.push_back(DAG.getBoolExtOrTrunc(ResultCarry, dl, CarryType, VT));
3426 break;
3427 }
3428 case ISD::SADDO:
3429 case ISD::SSUBO: {
3430 SDValue Result, Overflow;
3431 TLI.expandSADDSUBO(Node, Result, Overflow, DAG);
3432 Results.push_back(Result);
3433 Results.push_back(Overflow);
3434 break;
3435 }
3436 case ISD::UADDO:
3437 case ISD::USUBO: {
3438 SDValue Result, Overflow;
3439 TLI.expandUADDSUBO(Node, Result, Overflow, DAG);
3440 Results.push_back(Result);
3441 Results.push_back(Overflow);
3442 break;
3443 }
3444 case ISD::UMULO:
3445 case ISD::SMULO: {
3446 SDValue Result, Overflow;
3447 if (TLI.expandMULO(Node, Result, Overflow, DAG)) {
3448 Results.push_back(Result);
3449 Results.push_back(Overflow);
3450 }
3451 break;
3452 }
3453 case ISD::BUILD_PAIR: {
3454 EVT PairTy = Node->getValueType(0);
3455 Tmp1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::ZERO_EXTEND, dl, PairTy, Node->getOperand(0));
3456 Tmp2 = DAG.getNode(ISD::ANY_EXTEND, dl, PairTy, Node->getOperand(1));
3457 Tmp2 = DAG.getNode(
3458 ISD::SHL, dl, PairTy, Tmp2,
3459 DAG.getConstant(PairTy.getSizeInBits() / 2, dl,
3460 TLI.getShiftAmountTy(PairTy, DAG.getDataLayout())));
3461 Results.push_back(DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, dl, PairTy, Tmp1, Tmp2));
3462 break;
3463 }
3464 case ISD::SELECT:
3465 Tmp1 = Node->getOperand(0);
3466 Tmp2 = Node->getOperand(1);
3467 Tmp3 = Node->getOperand(2);
3468 if (Tmp1.getOpcode() == ISD::SETCC) {
3469 Tmp1 = DAG.getSelectCC(dl, Tmp1.getOperand(0), Tmp1.getOperand(1),
3470 Tmp2, Tmp3,
3471 cast<CondCodeSDNode>(Tmp1.getOperand(2))->get());
3472 } else {
3473 Tmp1 = DAG.getSelectCC(dl, Tmp1,
3474 DAG.getConstant(0, dl, Tmp1.getValueType()),
3475 Tmp2, Tmp3, ISD::SETNE);
3476 }
3477 Tmp1->setFlags(Node->getFlags());
3478 Results.push_back(Tmp1);
3479 break;
3480 case ISD::BR_JT: {
3481 SDValue Chain = Node->getOperand(0);
3482 SDValue Table = Node->getOperand(1);
3483 SDValue Index = Node->getOperand(2);
3484 assert(Index.getValueType().isInteger());
3485
3486 const DataLayout &TD = DAG.getDataLayout();
3487 EVT PTy = TLI.getPointerRangeTy(TD);
3488
3489 unsigned EntrySize =
3490 DAG.getMachineFunction().getJumpTableInfo()->getEntrySize(TD);
3491
3492 // For power-of-two jumptable entry sizes convert multiplication to a shift.
3493 // This transformation needs to be done here since otherwise the MIPS
3494 // backend will end up emitting a three instruction multiply sequence
3495 // instead of a single shift and MSP430 will call a runtime function.
3496 if (llvm::isPowerOf2_32(EntrySize))
3497 Index = DAG.getNode(
3498 ISD::SHL, dl, Index.getValueType(), Index,
3499 DAG.getConstant(llvm::Log2_32(EntrySize), dl, Index.getValueType()));
3500 else
3501 Index = DAG.getNode(ISD::MUL, dl, Index.getValueType(), Index,
3502 DAG.getConstant(EntrySize, dl, Index.getValueType()));
3503 SDValue Addr = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, dl, Index.getValueType(),
3504 Index, Table);
3505
3506 EVT MemVT = EVT::getIntegerVT(*DAG.getContext(), EntrySize * 8);
3507 SDValue LD = DAG.getExtLoad(
3508 ISD::SEXTLOAD, dl, PTy, Chain, Addr,
3509 MachinePointerInfo::getJumpTable(DAG.getMachineFunction()), MemVT);
3510 Addr = LD;
3511 if (TLI.isJumpTableRelative()) {
3512 // For PIC, the sequence is:
3513 // BRIND(load(Jumptable + index) + RelocBase)
3514 // RelocBase can be JumpTable, GOT or some sort of global base.
3515 Addr = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, dl, PTy, Addr,
3516 TLI.getPICJumpTableRelocBase(Table, DAG));
3517 }
3518
3519 Tmp1 = TLI.expandIndirectJTBranch(dl, LD.getValue(1), Addr, DAG);
3520 Results.push_back(Tmp1);
3521 break;
3522 }
3523 case ISD::BRCOND:
3524 // Expand brcond's setcc into its constituent parts and create a BR_CC
3525 // Node.
3526 Tmp1 = Node->getOperand(0);
3527 Tmp2 = Node->getOperand(1);
3528 if (Tmp2.getOpcode() == ISD::SETCC) {
3529 Tmp1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::BR_CC, dl, MVT::Other,
3530 Tmp1, Tmp2.getOperand(2),
3531 Tmp2.getOperand(0), Tmp2.getOperand(1),
3532 Node->getOperand(2));
3533 } else {
3534 // We test only the i1 bit. Skip the AND if UNDEF or another AND.
3535 if (Tmp2.isUndef() ||
3536 (Tmp2.getOpcode() == ISD::AND &&
3537 isa<ConstantSDNode>(Tmp2.getOperand(1)) &&
3538 cast<ConstantSDNode>(Tmp2.getOperand(1))->getZExtValue() == 1))
3539 Tmp3 = Tmp2;
3540 else
3541 Tmp3 = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, Tmp2.getValueType(), Tmp2,
3542 DAG.getConstant(1, dl, Tmp2.getValueType()));
3543 Tmp1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::BR_CC, dl, MVT::Other, Tmp1,
3544 DAG.getCondCode(ISD::SETNE), Tmp3,
3545 DAG.getConstant(0, dl, Tmp3.getValueType()),
3546 Node->getOperand(2));
3547 }
3548 Results.push_back(Tmp1);
3549 break;
3550 case ISD::SETCC: {
3551 Tmp1 = Node->getOperand(0);
3552 Tmp2 = Node->getOperand(1);
3553 Tmp3 = Node->getOperand(2);
3554 bool Legalized = LegalizeSetCCCondCode(Node->getValueType(0), Tmp1, Tmp2,
3555 Tmp3, NeedInvert, dl);
3556
3557 if (Legalized) {
3558 // If we expanded the SETCC by swapping LHS and RHS, or by inverting the
3559 // condition code, create a new SETCC node.
3560 if (Tmp3.getNode())
3561 Tmp1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::SETCC, dl, Node->getValueType(0),
3562 Tmp1, Tmp2, Tmp3, Node->getFlags());
3563
3564 // If we expanded the SETCC by inverting the condition code, then wrap
3565 // the existing SETCC in a NOT to restore the intended condition.
3566 if (NeedInvert)
3567 Tmp1 = DAG.getLogicalNOT(dl, Tmp1, Tmp1->getValueType(0));
3568
3569 Results.push_back(Tmp1);
3570 break;
3571 }
3572
3573 // Otherwise, SETCC for the given comparison type must be completely
3574 // illegal; expand it into a SELECT_CC.
3575 EVT VT = Node->getValueType(0);
3576 int TrueValue;
3577 switch (TLI.getBooleanContents(Tmp1.getValueType())) {
3578 case TargetLowering::ZeroOrOneBooleanContent:
3579 case TargetLowering::UndefinedBooleanContent:
3580 TrueValue = 1;
3581 break;
3582 case TargetLowering::ZeroOrNegativeOneBooleanContent:
3583 TrueValue = -1;
3584 break;
3585 }
3586 Tmp1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::SELECT_CC, dl, VT, Tmp1, Tmp2,
3587 DAG.getConstant(TrueValue, dl, VT),
3588 DAG.getConstant(0, dl, VT),
3589 Tmp3);
3590 Tmp1->setFlags(Node->getFlags());
3591 Results.push_back(Tmp1);
3592 break;
3593 }
3594 case ISD::SELECT_CC: {
3595 Tmp1 = Node->getOperand(0); // LHS
3596 Tmp2 = Node->getOperand(1); // RHS
3597 Tmp3 = Node->getOperand(2); // True
3598 Tmp4 = Node->getOperand(3); // False
3599 EVT VT = Node->getValueType(0);
3600 SDValue CC = Node->getOperand(4);
3601 ISD::CondCode CCOp = cast<CondCodeSDNode>(CC)->get();
3602
3603 if (TLI.isCondCodeLegalOrCustom(CCOp, Tmp1.getSimpleValueType())) {
3604 // If the condition code is legal, then we need to expand this
3605 // node using SETCC and SELECT.
3606 EVT CmpVT = Tmp1.getValueType();
3607 assert(!TLI.isOperationExpand(ISD::SELECT, VT) &&
3608 "Cannot expand ISD::SELECT_CC when ISD::SELECT also needs to be "
3609 "expanded.");
3610 EVT CCVT =
3611 TLI.getSetCCResultType(DAG.getDataLayout(), *DAG.getContext(), CmpVT);
3612 SDValue Cond = DAG.getNode(ISD::SETCC, dl, CCVT, Tmp1, Tmp2, CC, Node->getFlags());
3613 Results.push_back(DAG.getSelect(dl, VT, Cond, Tmp3, Tmp4));
3614 break;
3615 }
3616
3617 // SELECT_CC is legal, so the condition code must not be.
3618 bool Legalized = false;
3619 // Try to legalize by inverting the condition. This is for targets that
3620 // might support an ordered version of a condition, but not the unordered
3621 // version (or vice versa).
3622 ISD::CondCode InvCC = ISD::getSetCCInverse(CCOp,
3623 Tmp1.getValueType());
3624 if (TLI.isCondCodeLegalOrCustom(InvCC, Tmp1.getSimpleValueType())) {
3625 // Use the new condition code and swap true and false
3626 Legalized = true;
3627 Tmp1 = DAG.getSelectCC(dl, Tmp1, Tmp2, Tmp4, Tmp3, InvCC);
3628 } else {
3629 // If The inverse is not legal, then try to swap the arguments using
3630 // the inverse condition code.
3631 ISD::CondCode SwapInvCC = ISD::getSetCCSwappedOperands(InvCC);
3632 if (TLI.isCondCodeLegalOrCustom(SwapInvCC, Tmp1.getSimpleValueType())) {
3633 // The swapped inverse condition is legal, so swap true and false,
3634 // lhs and rhs.
3635 Legalized = true;
3636 Tmp1 = DAG.getSelectCC(dl, Tmp2, Tmp1, Tmp4, Tmp3, SwapInvCC);
3637 }
3638 }
3639
3640 if (!Legalized) {
3641 Legalized = LegalizeSetCCCondCode(
3642 getSetCCResultType(Tmp1.getValueType()), Tmp1, Tmp2, CC, NeedInvert,
3643 dl);
3644
3645 assert(Legalized && "Can't legalize SELECT_CC with legal condition!");
3646
3647 // If we expanded the SETCC by inverting the condition code, then swap
3648 // the True/False operands to match.
3649 if (NeedInvert)
3650 std::swap(Tmp3, Tmp4);
3651
3652 // If we expanded the SETCC by swapping LHS and RHS, or by inverting the
3653 // condition code, create a new SELECT_CC node.
3654 if (CC.getNode()) {
3655 Tmp1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::SELECT_CC, dl, Node->getValueType(0),
3656 Tmp1, Tmp2, Tmp3, Tmp4, CC);
3657 } else {
3658 Tmp2 = DAG.getConstant(0, dl, Tmp1.getValueType());
3659 CC = DAG.getCondCode(ISD::SETNE);
3660 Tmp1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::SELECT_CC, dl, Node->getValueType(0), Tmp1,
3661 Tmp2, Tmp3, Tmp4, CC);
3662 }
3663 }
3664 Results.push_back(Tmp1);
3665 break;
3666 }
3667 case ISD::BR_CC: {
3668 Tmp1 = Node->getOperand(0); // Chain
3669 Tmp2 = Node->getOperand(2); // LHS
3670 Tmp3 = Node->getOperand(3); // RHS
3671 Tmp4 = Node->getOperand(1); // CC
3672
3673 bool Legalized = LegalizeSetCCCondCode(getSetCCResultType(
3674 Tmp2.getValueType()), Tmp2, Tmp3, Tmp4, NeedInvert, dl);
3675 (void)Legalized;
3676 assert(Legalized && "Can't legalize BR_CC with legal condition!");
3677
3678 assert(!NeedInvert && "Don't know how to invert BR_CC!");
3679
3680 // If we expanded the SETCC by swapping LHS and RHS, create a new BR_CC
3681 // node.
3682 if (Tmp4.getNode()) {
3683 Tmp1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::BR_CC, dl, Node->getValueType(0), Tmp1,
3684 Tmp4, Tmp2, Tmp3, Node->getOperand(4));
3685 } else {
3686 Tmp3 = DAG.getConstant(0, dl, Tmp2.getValueType());
3687 Tmp4 = DAG.getCondCode(ISD::SETNE);
3688 Tmp1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::BR_CC, dl, Node->getValueType(0), Tmp1, Tmp4,
3689 Tmp2, Tmp3, Node->getOperand(4));
3690 }
3691 Results.push_back(Tmp1);
3692 break;
3693 }
3694 case ISD::BUILD_VECTOR:
3695 Results.push_back(ExpandBUILD_VECTOR(Node));
3696 break;
3697 case ISD::SRA:
3698 case ISD::SRL:
3699 case ISD::SHL: {
3700 // Scalarize vector SRA/SRL/SHL.
3701 EVT VT = Node->getValueType(0);
3702 assert(VT.isVector() && "Unable to legalize non-vector shift");
3703 assert(TLI.isTypeLegal(VT.getScalarType())&& "Element type must be legal");
3704 unsigned NumElem = VT.getVectorNumElements();
3705
3706 SmallVector<SDValue, 8> Scalars;
3707 for (unsigned Idx = 0; Idx < NumElem; Idx++) {
3708 SDValue Ex = DAG.getNode(
3709 ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, dl, VT.getScalarType(), Node->getOperand(0),
3710 DAG.getConstant(Idx, dl, TLI.getVectorIdxTy(DAG.getDataLayout())));
3711 SDValue Sh = DAG.getNode(
3712 ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, dl, VT.getScalarType(), Node->getOperand(1),
3713 DAG.getConstant(Idx, dl, TLI.getVectorIdxTy(DAG.getDataLayout())));
3714 Scalars.push_back(DAG.getNode(Node->getOpcode(), dl,
3715 VT.getScalarType(), Ex, Sh));
3716 }
3717
3718 SDValue Result = DAG.getBuildVector(Node->getValueType(0), dl, Scalars);
3719 ReplaceNode(SDValue(Node, 0), Result);
3720 break;
3721 }
3722 case ISD::VECREDUCE_FADD:
3723 case ISD::VECREDUCE_FMUL:
3724 case ISD::VECREDUCE_ADD:
3725 case ISD::VECREDUCE_MUL:
3726 case ISD::VECREDUCE_AND:
3727 case ISD::VECREDUCE_OR:
3728 case ISD::VECREDUCE_XOR:
3729 case ISD::VECREDUCE_SMAX:
3730 case ISD::VECREDUCE_SMIN:
3731 case ISD::VECREDUCE_UMAX:
3732 case ISD::VECREDUCE_UMIN:
3733 case ISD::VECREDUCE_FMAX:
3734 case ISD::VECREDUCE_FMIN:
3735 Results.push_back(TLI.expandVecReduce(Node, DAG));
3736 break;
3737 case ISD::GLOBAL_OFFSET_TABLE:
3738 case ISD::GlobalAddress:
3739 case ISD::GlobalTLSAddress:
3740 case ISD::ExternalSymbol:
3741 case ISD::ConstantPool:
3742 case ISD::JumpTable:
3743 case ISD::INTRINSIC_W_CHAIN:
3744 case ISD::INTRINSIC_WO_CHAIN:
3745 case ISD::INTRINSIC_VOID:
3746 // FIXME: Custom lowering for these operations shouldn't return null!
3747 break;
3748 }
3749
3750 // Replace the original node with the legalized result.
3751 if (Results.empty()) {
3752 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Cannot expand node\n");
3753 return false;
3754 }
3755
3756 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Successfully expanded node\n");
3757 ReplaceNode(Node, Results.data());
3758 return true;
3759}

3761void SelectionDAGLegalize::ConvertNodeToLibcall(SDNode *Node) {
3762 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Trying to convert node to libcall\n");
3763 SmallVector<SDValue, 8> Results;
3764 SDLoc dl(Node);
3765 // FIXME: Check flags on the node to see if we can use a finite call.
3766 bool CanUseFiniteLibCall = TM.Options.NoInfsFPMath && TM.Options.NoNaNsFPMath;
3767 unsigned Opc = Node->getOpcode();
3768 switch (Opc) {
3769 case ISD::ATOMIC_FENCE: {
3770 // If the target didn't lower this, lower it to '__sync_synchronize()' call
3771 // FIXME: handle "fence singlethread" more efficiently.
3772 TargetLowering::ArgListTy Args;
3773
3774 TargetLowering::CallLoweringInfo CLI(DAG);
3775 CLI.setDebugLoc(dl)
3776 .setChain(Node->getOperand(0))
3777 .setLibCallee(CallingConv::C, Type::getVoidTy(*DAG.getContext()),
3778 DAG.getExternalFunctionSymbol("__sync_synchronize"),
3779 std::move(Args));
3780
3781 std::pair<SDValue, SDValue> CallResult = TLI.LowerCallTo(CLI);
3782
3783 Results.push_back(CallResult.second);
3784 break;
3785 }
3786 // By default, atomic intrinsics are marked Legal and lowered. Targets
3787 // which don't support them directly, however, may want libcalls, in which
3788 // case they mark them Expand, and we get here.
3789 case ISD::ATOMIC_SWAP:
3790 case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_ADD:
3791 case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_SUB:
3792 case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_AND:
3793 case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_CLR:
3794 case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_OR:
3795 case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_XOR:
3796 case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_NAND:
3797 case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_MIN:
3798 case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_MAX:
3799 case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_UMIN:
3800 case ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_UMAX:
3801 case ISD::ATOMIC_CMP_SWAP: {
3802 MVT VT = cast<AtomicSDNode>(Node)->getMemoryVT().getSimpleVT();
3803 RTLIB::Libcall LC = RTLIB::getSYNC(Opc, VT);
3804 assert(LC != RTLIB::UNKNOWN_LIBCALL && "Unexpected atomic op or value type!");

3806 std::pair<SDValue, SDValue> Tmp = ExpandChainLibCall(LC, Node, false);
3807 Results.push_back(Tmp.first);
3808 Results.push_back(Tmp.second);

3818 DAG.getExternalFunctionSymbol("abort"), std::move(Args));

4089}

4091// Determine the vector type to use in place of an original scalar element when
4092// promoting equally sized vectors.
4093static MVT getPromotedVectorElementType(const TargetLowering &TLI,
4094 MVT EltVT, MVT NewEltVT) {
4095 unsigned OldEltsPerNewElt = EltVT.getSizeInBits() / NewEltVT.getSizeInBits();
4096 MVT MidVT = MVT::getVectorVT(NewEltVT, OldEltsPerNewElt);
4097 assert(TLI.isTypeLegal(MidVT) && "unexpected");
4098 return MidVT;
4099}
4100
4101void SelectionDAGLegalize::PromoteNode(SDNode *Node) {
4102 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Trying to promote node\n");
4103 SmallVector<SDValue, 8> Results;
4104 MVT OVT = Node->getSimpleValueType(0);
4105 if (Node->getOpcode() == ISD::UINT_TO_FP ||
4106 Node->getOpcode() == ISD::SINT_TO_FP ||
4107 Node->getOpcode() == ISD::SETCC ||
4108 Node->getOpcode() == ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT ||
4109 Node->getOpcode() == ISD::INSERT_VECTOR_ELT) {
4110 OVT = Node->getOperand(0).getSimpleValueType();
4111 }
4112 if (Node->getOpcode() == ISD::BR_CC)
4113 OVT = Node->getOperand(2).getSimpleValueType();
4114 MVT NVT = TLI.getTypeToPromoteTo(Node->getOpcode(), OVT);
4115 SDLoc dl(Node);
4116 SDValue Tmp1, Tmp2, Tmp3;
4117 switch (Node->getOpcode()) {
4118 case ISD::CTTZ:
4119 case ISD::CTTZ_ZERO_UNDEF:
4120 case ISD::CTLZ:
4121 case ISD::CTLZ_ZERO_UNDEF:
4122 case ISD::CTPOP:
4123 // Zero extend the argument.
4124 Tmp1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::ZERO_EXTEND, dl, NVT, Node->getOperand(0));
4125 if (Node->getOpcode() == ISD::CTTZ) {
4126 // The count is the same in the promoted type except if the original
4127 // value was zero. This can be handled by setting the bit just off
4128 // the top of the original type.
4129 auto TopBit = APInt::getOneBitSet(NVT.getSizeInBits(),
4130 OVT.getSizeInBits());
4131 Tmp1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, dl, NVT, Tmp1,
4132 DAG.getConstant(TopBit, dl, NVT));
4133 }
4134 // Perform the larger operation. For CTPOP and CTTZ_ZERO_UNDEF, this is
4135 // already the correct result.
4136 Tmp1 = DAG.getNode(Node->getOpcode(), dl, NVT, Tmp1);
4137 if (Node->getOpcode() == ISD::CTLZ ||
4138 Node->getOpcode() == ISD::CTLZ_ZERO_UNDEF) {
4139 // Tmp1 = Tmp1 - (sizeinbits(NVT) - sizeinbits(Old VT))
4140 Tmp1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::SUB, dl, NVT, Tmp1,
4141 DAG.getConstant(NVT.getSizeInBits() -
4142 OVT.getSizeInBits(), dl, NVT));
4143 }
4144 Results.push_back(DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, dl, OVT, Tmp1));
4145 break;
4146 case ISD::BITREVERSE:
4147 case ISD::BSWAP: {
4148 unsigned DiffBits = NVT.getSizeInBits() - OVT.getSizeInBits();
4149 Tmp1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::ZERO_EXTEND, dl, NVT, Node->getOperand(0));
4150 Tmp1 = DAG.getNode(Node->getOpcode(), dl, NVT, Tmp1);
4151 Tmp1 = DAG.getNode(
4152 ISD::SRL, dl, NVT, Tmp1,
4153 DAG.getConstant(DiffBits, dl,
4154 TLI.getShiftAmountTy(NVT, DAG.getDataLayout())));
4155
4156 Results.push_back(DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, dl, OVT, Tmp1));
4157 break;
4158 }
4159 case ISD::FP_TO_UINT:
4160 case ISD::FP_TO_SINT:
4161 Tmp1 = PromoteLegalFP_TO_INT(Node->getOperand(0), Node->getValueType(0),
4162 Node->getOpcode() == ISD::FP_TO_SINT, dl);
4163 Results.push_back(Tmp1);
4164 break;
4165 case ISD::UINT_TO_FP:
4166 case ISD::SINT_TO_FP:
4167 Tmp1 = PromoteLegalINT_TO_FP(Node->getOperand(0), Node->getValueType(0),
4168 Node->getOpcode() == ISD::SINT_TO_FP, dl);
4169 Results.push_back(Tmp1);
4170 break;
4171 case ISD::VAARG: {
4172 SDValue Chain = Node->getOperand(0); // Get the chain.
4173 SDValue Ptr = Node->getOperand(1); // Get the pointer.
4174
4175 unsigned TruncOp;
4176 if (OVT.isVector()) {
4177 TruncOp = ISD::BITCAST;
4178 } else {
4179 assert(OVT.isInteger()
4180 && "VAARG promotion is supported only for vectors or integer types");
4181 TruncOp = ISD::TRUNCATE;
4182 }
4183
4184 // Perform the larger operation, then convert back
4185 Tmp1 = DAG.getVAArg(NVT, dl, Chain, Ptr, Node->getOperand(2),
4186 Node->getConstantOperandVal(3));
4187 Chain = Tmp1.getValue(1);
4188
4189 Tmp2 = DAG.getNode(TruncOp, dl, OVT, Tmp1);
4190
4191 // Modified the chain result - switch anything that used the old chain to
4192 // use the new one.
4193 DAG.ReplaceAllUsesOfValueWith(SDValue(Node, 0), Tmp2);
4194 DAG.ReplaceAllUsesOfValueWith(SDValue(Node, 1), Chain);
4195 if (UpdatedNodes) {
4196 UpdatedNodes->insert(Tmp2.getNode());
4197 UpdatedNodes->insert(Chain.getNode());
4198 }
4199 ReplacedNode(Node);
4200 break;
4201 }
4202 case ISD::MUL:
4203 case ISD::SDIV:
4204 case ISD::SREM:
4205 case ISD::UDIV:
4206 case ISD::UREM:
4207 case ISD::AND:
4208 case ISD::OR:
4209 case ISD::XOR: {
4210 unsigned ExtOp, TruncOp;
4211 if (OVT.isVector()) {
4212 ExtOp = ISD::BITCAST;
4213 TruncOp = ISD::BITCAST;
4214 } else {
4215 assert(OVT.isInteger() && "Cannot promote logic operation");
4216
4217 switch (Node->getOpcode()) {
4218 default:
4219 ExtOp = ISD::ANY_EXTEND;
4220 break;
4221 case ISD::SDIV:
4222 case ISD::SREM:
4223 ExtOp = ISD::SIGN_EXTEND;
4224 break;
4225 case ISD::UDIV:
4226 case ISD::UREM:
4227 ExtOp = ISD::ZERO_EXTEND;
4228 break;
4229 }
4230 TruncOp = ISD::TRUNCATE;
4231 }
4232 // Promote each of the values to the new type.
4233 Tmp1 = DAG.getNode(ExtOp, dl, NVT, Node->getOperand(0));
4234 Tmp2 = DAG.getNode(ExtOp, dl, NVT, Node->getOperand(1));
4235 // Perform the larger operation, then convert back
4236 Tmp1 = DAG.getNode(Node->getOpcode(), dl, NVT, Tmp1, Tmp2);
4237 Results.push_back(DAG.getNode(TruncOp, dl, OVT, Tmp1));
4238 break;
4239 }
4240 case ISD::UMUL_LOHI:
4241 case ISD::SMUL_LOHI: {
4242 // Promote to a multiply in a wider integer type.
4243 unsigned ExtOp = Node->getOpcode() == ISD::UMUL_LOHI ? ISD::ZERO_EXTEND
4244 : ISD::SIGN_EXTEND;
4245 Tmp1 = DAG.getNode(ExtOp, dl, NVT, Node->getOperand(0));
4246 Tmp2 = DAG.getNode(ExtOp, dl, NVT, Node->getOperand(1));
4247 Tmp1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::MUL, dl, NVT, Tmp1, Tmp2);
4248
4249 auto &DL = DAG.getDataLayout();
4250 unsigned OriginalSize = OVT.getScalarSizeInBits();
4251 Tmp2 = DAG.getNode(
4252 ISD::SRL, dl, NVT, Tmp1,
4253 DAG.getConstant(OriginalSize, dl, TLI.getScalarShiftAmountTy(DL, NVT)));
4254 Results.push_back(DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, dl, OVT, Tmp1));
4255 Results.push_back(DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, dl, OVT, Tmp2));
4256 break;
4257 }
4258 case ISD::SELECT: {
4259 unsigned ExtOp, TruncOp;
4260 if (Node->getValueType(0).isVector() ||
4261 Node->getValueType(0).getSizeInBits() == NVT.getSizeInBits()) {
4262 ExtOp = ISD::BITCAST;
4263 TruncOp = ISD::BITCAST;
4264 } else if (Node->getValueType(0).isInteger()) {
4265 ExtOp = ISD::ANY_EXTEND;
4266 TruncOp = ISD::TRUNCATE;
4267 } else {
4268 ExtOp = ISD::FP_EXTEND;
4269 TruncOp = ISD::FP_ROUND;
4270 }
4271 Tmp1 = Node->getOperand(0);
4272 // Promote each of the values to the new type.
4273 Tmp2 = DAG.getNode(ExtOp, dl, NVT, Node->getOperand(1));
4274 Tmp3 = DAG.getNode(ExtOp, dl, NVT, Node->getOperand(2));
4275 // Perform the larger operation, then round down.
4276 Tmp1 = DAG.getSelect(dl, NVT, Tmp1, Tmp2, Tmp3);
4277 Tmp1->setFlags(Node->getFlags());
4278 if (TruncOp != ISD::FP_ROUND)
4279 Tmp1 = DAG.getNode(TruncOp, dl, Node->getValueType(0), Tmp1);
4280 else
4281 Tmp1 = DAG.getNode(TruncOp, dl, Node->getValueType(0), Tmp1,
4282 DAG.getIntPtrConstant(0, dl));
4283 Results.push_back(Tmp1);
4284 break;
4285 }
4286 case ISD::VECTOR_SHUFFLE: {
4287 ArrayRef<int> Mask = cast<ShuffleVectorSDNode>(Node)->getMask();
4288
4289 // Cast the two input vectors.
4290 Tmp1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, dl, NVT, Node->getOperand(0));
4291 Tmp2 = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, dl, NVT, Node->getOperand(1));
4292
4293 // Convert the shuffle mask to the right # elements.
4294 Tmp1 = ShuffleWithNarrowerEltType(NVT, OVT, dl, Tmp1, Tmp2, Mask);
4295 Tmp1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, dl, OVT, Tmp1);
4296 Results.push_back(Tmp1);
4297 break;
4298 }
4299 case ISD::SETCC: {
4300 unsigned ExtOp = ISD::FP_EXTEND;
4301 if (NVT.isInteger()) {
4302 ISD::CondCode CCCode =
4303 cast<CondCodeSDNode>(Node->getOperand(2))->get();
4304 ExtOp = isSignedIntSetCC(CCCode) ? ISD::SIGN_EXTEND : ISD::ZERO_EXTEND;
4305 }
4306 Tmp1 = DAG.getNode(ExtOp, dl, NVT, Node->getOperand(0));
4307 Tmp2 = DAG.getNode(ExtOp, dl, NVT, Node->getOperand(1));
4308 Results.push_back(DAG.getNode(ISD::SETCC, dl, Node->getValueType(0), Tmp1,
4309 Tmp2, Node->getOperand(2), Node->getFlags()));
4310 break;
4311 }
4312 case ISD::BR_CC: {
4313 unsigned ExtOp = ISD::FP_EXTEND;
4314 if (NVT.isInteger()) {
4315 ISD::CondCode CCCode =
4316 cast<CondCodeSDNode>(Node->getOperand(1))->get();
4317 ExtOp = isSignedIntSetCC(CCCode) ? ISD::SIGN_EXTEND : ISD::ZERO_EXTEND;
4318 }
4319 Tmp1 = DAG.getNode(ExtOp, dl, NVT, Node->getOperand(2));
4320 Tmp2 = DAG.getNode(ExtOp, dl, NVT, Node->getOperand(3));
4321 Results.push_back(DAG.getNode(ISD::BR_CC, dl, Node->getValueType(0),
4322 Node->getOperand(0), Node->getOperand(1),
4323 Tmp1, Tmp2, Node->getOperand(4)));
4324 break;
4325 }
4326 case ISD::FADD:
4327 case ISD::FSUB:
4328 case ISD::FMUL:
4329 case ISD::FDIV:
4330 case ISD::FREM:
4331 case ISD::FMINNUM:
4332 case ISD::FMAXNUM:
4333 case ISD::FPOW:
4334 Tmp1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::FP_EXTEND, dl, NVT, Node->getOperand(0));
4335 Tmp2 = DAG.getNode(ISD::FP_EXTEND, dl, NVT, Node->getOperand(1));
4336 Tmp3 = DAG.getNode(Node->getOpcode(), dl, NVT, Tmp1, Tmp2,
4337 Node->getFlags());
4338 Results.push_back(DAG.getNode(ISD::FP_ROUND, dl, OVT,
4339 Tmp3, DAG.getIntPtrConstant(0, dl)));
4340 break;
4341 case ISD::FMA:
4342 Tmp1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::FP_EXTEND, dl, NVT, Node->getOperand(0));
4343 Tmp2 = DAG.getNode(ISD::FP_EXTEND, dl, NVT, Node->getOperand(1));
4344 Tmp3 = DAG.getNode(ISD::FP_EXTEND, dl, NVT, Node->getOperand(2));
4345 Results.push_back(
4346 DAG.getNode(ISD::FP_ROUND, dl, OVT,
4347 DAG.getNode(Node->getOpcode(), dl, NVT, Tmp1, Tmp2, Tmp3),
4348 DAG.getIntPtrConstant(0, dl)));
4349 break;
4350 case ISD::FCOPYSIGN:
4351 case ISD::FPOWI: {
4352 Tmp1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::FP_EXTEND, dl, NVT, Node->getOperand(0));
4353 Tmp2 = Node->getOperand(1);
4354 Tmp3 = DAG.getNode(Node->getOpcode(), dl, NVT, Tmp1, Tmp2);
4355
4356 // fcopysign doesn't change anything but the sign bit, so
4357 // (fp_round (fcopysign (fpext a), b))
4358 // is as precise as
4359 // (fp_round (fpext a))
4360 // which is a no-op. Mark it as a TRUNCating FP_ROUND.
4361 const bool isTrunc = (Node->getOpcode() == ISD::FCOPYSIGN);
4362 Results.push_back(DAG.getNode(ISD::FP_ROUND, dl, OVT,
4363 Tmp3, DAG.getIntPtrConstant(isTrunc, dl)));
4364 break;
4365 }
4366 case ISD::FFLOOR:
4367 case ISD::FCEIL:
4368 case ISD::FRINT:
4369 case ISD::FNEARBYINT:
4370 case ISD::FROUND:
4371 case ISD::FTRUNC:
4372 case ISD::FNEG:
4373 case ISD::FSQRT:
4374 case ISD::FSIN:
4375 case ISD::FCOS:
4376 case ISD::FLOG:
4377 case ISD::FLOG2:
4378 case ISD::FLOG10:
4379 case ISD::FABS:
4380 case ISD::FEXP:
4381 case ISD::FEXP2:
4382 Tmp1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::FP_EXTEND, dl, NVT, Node->getOperand(0));
4383 Tmp2 = DAG.getNode(Node->getOpcode(), dl, NVT, Tmp1);
4384 Results.push_back(DAG.getNode(ISD::FP_ROUND, dl, OVT,
4385 Tmp2, DAG.getIntPtrConstant(0, dl)));
4386 break;
4387 case ISD::BUILD_VECTOR: {
4388 MVT EltVT = OVT.getVectorElementType();
4389 MVT NewEltVT = NVT.getVectorElementType();
4390
4391 // Handle bitcasts to a different vector type with the same total bit size
4392 //
4393 // e.g. v2i64 = build_vector i64:x, i64:y => v4i32
4394 // =>
4395 // v4i32 = concat_vectors (v2i32 (bitcast i64:x)), (v2i32 (bitcast i64:y))
4396
4397 assert(NVT.isVector() && OVT.getSizeInBits() == NVT.getSizeInBits() &&
4398 "Invalid promote type for build_vector");
4399 assert(NewEltVT.bitsLT(EltVT) && "not handled");
4400
4401 MVT MidVT = getPromotedVectorElementType(TLI, EltVT, NewEltVT);
4402
4403 SmallVector<SDValue, 8> NewOps;
4404 for (unsigned I = 0, E = Node->getNumOperands(); I != E; ++I) {
4405 SDValue Op = Node->getOperand(I);
4406 NewOps.push_back(DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, SDLoc(Op), MidVT, Op));
4407 }
4408
4409 SDLoc SL(Node);
4410 SDValue Concat = DAG.getNode(ISD::CONCAT_VECTORS, SL, NVT, NewOps);
4411 SDValue CvtVec = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, SL, OVT, Concat);
4412 Results.push_back(CvtVec);
4413 break;
4414 }
4415 case ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT: {
4416 MVT EltVT = OVT.getVectorElementType();
4417 MVT NewEltVT = NVT.getVectorElementType();
4418
4419 // Handle bitcasts to a different vector type with the same total bit size.
4420 //
4421 // e.g. v2i64 = extract_vector_elt x:v2i64, y:i32
4422 // =>
4423 // v4i32:castx = bitcast x:v2i64
4424 //
4425 // i64 = bitcast
4426 // (v2i32 build_vector (i32 (extract_vector_elt castx, (2 * y))),
4427 // (i32 (extract_vector_elt castx, (2 * y + 1)))
4428 //
4429
4430 assert(NVT.isVector() && OVT.getSizeInBits() == NVT.getSizeInBits() &&
4431 "Invalid promote type for extract_vector_elt");
4432 assert(NewEltVT.bitsLT(EltVT) && "not handled");
4433
4434 MVT MidVT = getPromotedVectorElementType(TLI, EltVT, NewEltVT);
4435 unsigned NewEltsPerOldElt = MidVT.getVectorNumElements();
4436
4437 SDValue Idx = Node->getOperand(1);
4438 EVT IdxVT = Idx.getValueType();
4439 SDLoc SL(Node);
4440 SDValue Factor = DAG.getConstant(NewEltsPerOldElt, SL, IdxVT);
4441 SDValue NewBaseIdx = DAG.getNode(ISD::MUL, SL, IdxVT, Idx, Factor);
4442
4443 SDValue CastVec = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, SL, NVT, Node->getOperand(0));
4444
4445 SmallVector<SDValue, 8> NewOps;
4446 for (unsigned I = 0; I < NewEltsPerOldElt; ++I) {
4447 SDValue IdxOffset = DAG.getConstant(I, SL, IdxVT);
4448 SDValue TmpIdx = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, SL, IdxVT, NewBaseIdx, IdxOffset);
4449
4450 SDValue Elt = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, SL, NewEltVT,
4451 CastVec, TmpIdx);
4452 NewOps.push_back(Elt);
4453 }
4454
4455 SDValue NewVec = DAG.getBuildVector(MidVT, SL, NewOps);
4456 Results.push_back(DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, SL, EltVT, NewVec));
4457 break;
4458 }
4459 case ISD::INSERT_VECTOR_ELT: {
4460 MVT EltVT = OVT.getVectorElementType();
4461 MVT NewEltVT = NVT.getVectorElementType();
4462
4463 // Handle bitcasts to a different vector type with the same total bit size
4464 //
4465 // e.g. v2i64 = insert_vector_elt x:v2i64, y:i64, z:i32
4466 // =>
4467 // v4i32:castx = bitcast x:v2i64
4468 // v2i32:casty = bitcast y:i64
4469 //
4470 // v2i64 = bitcast
4471 // (v4i32 insert_vector_elt
4472 // (v4i32 insert_vector_elt v4i32:castx,
4473 // (extract_vector_elt casty, 0), 2 * z),
4474 // (extract_vector_elt casty, 1), (2 * z + 1))
4475
4476 assert(NVT.isVector() && OVT.getSizeInBits() == NVT.getSizeInBits() &&
4477 "Invalid promote type for insert_vector_elt");
4478 assert(NewEltVT.bitsLT(EltVT) && "not handled");
4479
4480 MVT MidVT = getPromotedVectorElementType(TLI, EltVT, NewEltVT);
4481 unsigned NewEltsPerOldElt = MidVT.getVectorNumElements();
4482
4483 SDValue Val = Node->getOperand(1);
4484 SDValue Idx = Node->getOperand(2);
4485 EVT IdxVT = Idx.getValueType();
4486 SDLoc SL(Node);
4487
4488 SDValue Factor = DAG.getConstant(NewEltsPerOldElt, SDLoc(), IdxVT);
4489 SDValue NewBaseIdx = DAG.getNode(ISD::MUL, SL, IdxVT, Idx, Factor);
4490
4491 SDValue CastVec = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, SL, NVT, Node->getOperand(0));
4492 SDValue CastVal = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, SL, MidVT, Val);
4493
4494 SDValue NewVec = CastVec;
4495 for (unsigned I = 0; I < NewEltsPerOldElt; ++I) {
4496 SDValue IdxOffset = DAG.getConstant(I, SL, IdxVT);
4497 SDValue InEltIdx = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, SL, IdxVT, NewBaseIdx, IdxOffset);
4498
4499 SDValue Elt = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, SL, NewEltVT,
4500 CastVal, IdxOffset);
4501
4502 NewVec = DAG.getNode(ISD::INSERT_VECTOR_ELT, SL, NVT,
4503 NewVec, Elt, InEltIdx);
4504 }
4505
4506 Results.push_back(DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, SL, OVT, NewVec));
4507 break;
4508 }
4509 case ISD::SCALAR_TO_VECTOR: {
4510 MVT EltVT = OVT.getVectorElementType();
4511 MVT NewEltVT = NVT.getVectorElementType();
4512
4513 // Handle bitcasts to different vector type with the same total bit size.
4514 //
4515 // e.g. v2i64 = scalar_to_vector x:i64
4516 // =>
4517 // concat_vectors (v2i32 bitcast x:i64), (v2i32 undef)
4518 //
4519
4520 MVT MidVT = getPromotedVectorElementType(TLI, EltVT, NewEltVT);
4521 SDValue Val = Node->getOperand(0);
4522 SDLoc SL(Node);
4523
4524 SDValue CastVal = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, SL, MidVT, Val);
4525 SDValue Undef = DAG.getUNDEF(MidVT);
4526
4527 SmallVector<SDValue, 8> NewElts;
4528 NewElts.push_back(CastVal);
4529 for (unsigned I = 1, NElts = OVT.getVectorNumElements(); I != NElts; ++I)
4530 NewElts.push_back(Undef);
4531
4532 SDValue Concat = DAG.getNode(ISD::CONCAT_VECTORS, SL, NVT, NewElts);
4533 SDValue CvtVec = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, SL, OVT, Concat);
4534 Results.push_back(CvtVec);
4535 break;
4536 }
4537 case ISD::ATOMIC_SWAP: {
4538 AtomicSDNode *AM = cast<AtomicSDNode>(Node);
4539 SDLoc SL(Node);
4540 SDValue CastVal = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, SL, NVT, AM->getVal());
4541 assert(NVT.getSizeInBits() == OVT.getSizeInBits() &&
4542 "unexpected promotion type");
4543 assert(AM->getMemoryVT().getSizeInBits() == NVT.getSizeInBits() &&
4544 "unexpected atomic_swap with illegal type");
4545
4546 SDValue NewAtomic
4547 = DAG.getAtomic(ISD::ATOMIC_SWAP, SL, NVT,
4548 DAG.getVTList(NVT, MVT::Other),
4549 { AM->getChain(), AM->getBasePtr(), CastVal },
4550 AM->getMemOperand());
4551 Results.push_back(DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, SL, OVT, NewAtomic));
4552 Results.push_back(NewAtomic.getValue(1));
4553 break;
4554 }
4555 }
4556
4557 // Replace the original node with the legalized result.
4558 if (!Results.empty()) {
4559 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Successfully promoted node\n");
4560 ReplaceNode(Node, Results.data());
4561 } else
4562 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Could not promote node\n");
4563}
4564
4565/// This is the entry point for the file.
4566void SelectionDAG::Legalize() {
4567 AssignTopologicalOrder();
4568
4569 SmallPtrSet<SDNode *, 16> LegalizedNodes;
4570 // Use a delete listener to remove nodes which were deleted during
4571 // legalization from LegalizeNodes. This is needed to handle the situation
4572 // where a new node is allocated by the object pool to the same address of a
4573 // previously deleted node.
4574 DAGNodeDeletedListener DeleteListener(
4575 *this,
4576 [&LegalizedNodes](SDNode *N, SDNode *E) { LegalizedNodes.erase(N); });
4577
4578 SelectionDAGLegalize Legalizer(*this, LegalizedNodes);
4579
4580 // Visit all the nodes. We start in topological order, so that we see
4581 // nodes with their original operands intact. Legalization can produce
4582 // new nodes which may themselves need to be legalized. Iterate until all
4583 // nodes have been legalized.
4584 while (true) {
4585 bool AnyLegalized = false;
4586 for (auto NI = allnodes_end(); NI != allnodes_begin();) {
4587 --NI;
4588
4589 SDNode *N = &*NI;
4590 if (N->use_empty() && N != getRoot().getNode()) {
4591 ++NI;
4592 DeleteNode(N);
4593 continue;
4594 }
4595
4596 if (LegalizedNodes.insert(N).second) {
4597 AnyLegalized = true;
4598 Legalizer.LegalizeOp(N);
4599
4600 if (N->use_empty() && N != getRoot().getNode()) {
4601 ++NI;
4602 DeleteNode(N);
4603 }
4604 }
4605 }
4606 if (!AnyLegalized)
4607 break;
4608
4609 }
4610
4611 // Remove dead nodes now.
4612 RemoveDeadNodes();
4613}
4614
4615bool SelectionDAG::LegalizeOp(SDNode *N,
4616 SmallSetVector<SDNode *, 16> &UpdatedNodes) {
4617 SmallPtrSet<SDNode *, 16> LegalizedNodes;
4618 SelectionDAGLegalize Legalizer(*this, LegalizedNodes, &UpdatedNodes);
4619
4620 // Directly insert the node in question, and legalize it. This will recurse
4621 // as needed through operands.
4622 LegalizedNodes.insert(N);
4623 Legalizer.LegalizeOp(N);
4624
4625 return LegalizedNodes.count(N);
4626}
